nd charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (1983)\n!Rank\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Austria ([[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jahreshitparade 1983 |publisher= Austriancharts.at. Hung Medien |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://www.austriancharts.at/1983_single.asp |language= de}}</ref>\n|17\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Belgium ([[Ultratop|Ultratop 50]] Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|title= Jaaroverzichten 1983 |publisher= [[Ultratop]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=1983 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|27\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Germany ([[GfK Entertainment Charts|Official German Charts]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jahrescharts \u2013 1983 |publisher= Offiziellecharts.de. [[GfK Entertainment Charts]] |url= https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1983 |archivedate= 9 May 2015 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150509000529/https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-1983 |language= de}}</ref>\n|2\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands ([[Dutch Top 40]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 1983 |publisher= [[Dutch Top 40]] |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/1983 |language= nl}}</ref>\n|14\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 1983 |publisher= [[Single Top 100]]. Hung Medien |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=1983&cat=s |language= nl}}</ref>\n|5\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Switzerland ([[Swiss Hitparade|Schweizer Hitparade]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Schweizer Jahreshitparade 1983 |publisher= Hitparade.ch. Hung Medien |url= http://hitparade.ch/year.asp?key=1983 |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |language= de}}</ref>\n|6\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (1984)\n!Rank\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Australia ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Forum \u2013 ARIA Charts: Special Occasion Charts \u2013 Top 100 End of Year AMR Charts \u2013 1980s |url= http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 |publisher=Australian-charts.com. Hung Medien |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141006134948/http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 |archivedate= 6 October 2014}}</ref>\n|18\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|France ([[Institut fran\u00e7ais d'opinion publique|IFOP]])<ref>{{cite web|title= TOP \u2013 1984 |publisher= Top-france.fr |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://www.top-france.fr/html/annuel/1984.htm |language= fr}}</ref>\n|16\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]<ref>{{cite web|title= Top 100 Hits for 1984 |publisher= The Longbored Surfer |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/1984}}</ref>\n|28\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/80s_files/1984YESP.html |title= The CASH BOX Year-End Charts: 1984 |url-status= dead |magazine= [[Cashbox (magazine)|Cash Box]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120930234839/http://cashboxmagazine.com/archives/80s_files/1984YESP.html |archivedate= 30 September 2012}}</ref>\n|31\n|}\n\n====Certifications and sales====\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=France|type=single|artist=Nena|title=99 Luftballons|award=Gold|relyear=1983|certyear=1983|certref=<ref>{{cite web|title= Les Singles / Titres Certifi\u00e9s \"Or\" |url= http://www.infodisc.fr/Chanson_Certification_Or.php?debut=450 |website= InfoDisc |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |language= fr}}</ref>|salesamount=666,500|salesref=<ref>{{cite web|title= Les Meilleures Ventes \"Tout Temps\" de 45 T. / Singles / T\u00e9l\u00e9chargement |url= http://www.infodisc.fr/Ventes_Chansons_Tout_Temps.php?debut=200 |website= InfoDisc |accessdate= 13 May 2016 |language= fr}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|type=single|artist=Nena|title=99 Luftballons|award=Gold|relyear=1983|certyear=1983}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Netherlands|type=single|artist=Nena|title=99 Luftballons|award=Gold|relyear=1983|certyear=1983|accessdate=26 June 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=single|artist=Nena|title=99 Luft Ballons|award=Gold|relyear=1984|certyear=1984}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===English version===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Weekly charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (1984)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|1|chartid=4454|accessdate=6 July 2011|rowheader=true|refname=\"Canada\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland2|1|artist=Nena|accessdate=6 July 2011|rowheader=true|refname=\"IRL\"}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|1|date=1984-03-03|accessdate=17 July 2014|rowheader=true|refname=\"UK\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|South Africa ([[Springbok Radio]])<ref>{{cite web|title= South African Rock Lists Website SA Charts 1969 \u2013 1989 Acts (N) |website= Rock.co.za |url= http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(N).html |accessdate= 21 June 2013}}</ref>\n|3\n|}\n\n====Year-end charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (1984)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Canada Top Singles (''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'')<ref>{{cite magazine|title= Top 100 Singles of 1984 |magazine= [[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |volume= 41 |issue= 17 |date= 5 January 1985 |accessdate= 17 July 2014 |url= http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.9638&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.9638.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.9638}}</ref>\n|13\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Certifications and sales====\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Canada|type=single|artist=Nena|title=99 Red Balloons|award=Platinum|relyear=1984|certyear=1984|salesamount=100,000}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|type=single|artist=Nena|title=99 Red Balloons|award=Gold|relyear=1984|certyear=1984}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===2002 re-release===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Chart (2002)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders Tip|17|artist=Nena|song=99 Luftballons [2002]|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 June 2013}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|28|artist=Nena|song=99 Luftballons|songid=922|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 June 2013}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Netherlands ([[Single Top 100]])<ref>{{cite web|title= Dutchcharts.nl \u2013 Nena \u2013 99 Luftballons |publisher= [[Single Top 100]] |language= nl |url= http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Nena&titel=99+Luftballons+%5B2002%5D&cat=s |accessdate= 17 July 2014}}</ref>\n|82\n|-\n{{singlechart|Swiss|77|artist=Nena|song=99 Luftballons [2002]|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 June 2013}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* [[List of anti-war songs]]\n* [[Lists of number-one singles (Austria)]]\n* [[List of number-one singles in Australia during the 1980s#1984 (Kent Music Report)|List of number-one singles in Australia during the 1980s]]\n* [[List of number-one singles of 1984 (Canada)]]\n* [[List of Cash Box Top 100 number-one singles of 1984|List of ''Cash Box'' Top 100 number-one singles of 1984]]\n{{col-2}}\n* [[List of Dutch Top 40 number-one singles of 1983]]\n* [[List of European number-one hits of 1983]]\n* [[List of number-one hits of 1983 (Germany)]]\n* [[List of number-one singles of 1984 (Ireland)]]\n* [[List of number-one singles from the 1980s (New Zealand)]]\n* [[List of number-one singles and albums in Sweden]]\n* [[List of number-one singles of the 1980s (Switzerland)#1983|List of number-one singles of the 1980s (Switzerland)]]\n* [[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 1980s#1984|List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 1980s]]\n* [[List of one-hit wonders in the United States]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|nena|99-luftballons-german}}\n\n{{Nena|top=yes}}\n\n[[Category:1983 songs]]\n[[Category:1983 singles]]\n[[Category:1984 singles]]\n[[Category:Nena (band) songs]]\n[[Category:Goldfinger (band) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by J\u00f6rn-Uwe Fahrenkrog-Petersen]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records singles]]\n[[Category:Epic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Dutch Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Single Top 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:European Hot 100 Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Australia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Austria]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Oricon International Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:RPM Top Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Ultratop 50 Singles (Flanders) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:German-language songs]]\n[[Category:Anti-war songs]]\n[[Category:Protest songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about aviation]]\n[[Category:Songs about nuclear war and weapons]]\n[[Category:Songs about the military]]\n[[Category:Balloons (entertainment)]]\n[[Category:Cold War in popular culture]]\n", "name_user": "2604:2000:1103:a0a2:ec46:74ab:cbf5:9da8", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/99_Luftballons"}
{"title_page": "Luiz Fernando Carvalho", "text_new": "{{infobox person\n| name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho\n| image    =\n| imagesize =\n| birth_name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho de Almeida\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|7|28|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality =\n| alias =\n| yearsactive = 1985\u2013present\n| occupation       = Film director, screenwriter, novelist\n| known_for        = [[Film]]s and [[Television program|TV series]] based on [[List of Brazilian writers|Brazilian writers]]\n| notable_works   =  ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|Os Maias]]'', ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]''\n| children = \n}}\n\n'''Luiz Fernando Carvalho''' (born July 28, 1960 in [[Rio de Janeiro]]) is a [[Brazil]]ian filmmaker and television director, known for works closely linked to literature that constitute a renovation in Brazilian audiovisual aesthetics.<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://escholarship.org/uc/item/589368qf#page-3 \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho: An Auteur of Brazilian Television\"], ''UCLA Electronic Theses and Dissertations'', 2013. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref> He has already brought to the screen works by [[Ariano Suassuna]], [[Raduan Nassar]], [[Machado de Assis]], [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]], [[Roland Barthes]], [[Clarice Lispector]], [[Milton Hatoum]], [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and [[Graciliano Ramos]], among others.\n\nSome critics compare Luiz Fernando Carvalho's productions to the Brazilian Cinema Novo<ref name=\"Sukman\">{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=lavoura+arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=Mario+Peixoto&decadaSelecionada=&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Um cineasta que est\u00e1 entrando para o clube dos poetas|author=Hugo Sukman|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho respeita uma tradi\u00e7\u00e3o que vai de Mario Peixoto a Ruy Guerra}}</ref> and icons of film history such as [[Luchino Visconti]] and [[Andrei Tarkovski]].<ref name=\"Piza\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-estreia-sabado-no-canada,20010822p2443|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" estr\u00e9ia s\u00e1bado no Canad\u00e1|author=Daniel Piza|date=22 August 2001|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um parentesco com o estilo e a espiritualidade do cinema dos russos Tarkovski e Sokurov}}</ref> His work is characterized by visual and linguistic experimentation<ref name=\"Ismail\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrissima/2016/10/1822788-quinze-anos-depois-filme-lavoura-arcaica-ainda-e-corpo-estranho.shtml|title=Quinze anos depois, filme \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ainda \u00e9 corpo estranho|author=Ilana Feldman e Ismail Xavier|date=16 October 2016|publisher=Ilustr\u00edssima/Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and exploration of the multiplicity of Brazil's cultural identity.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil\"], ''La N\u00e1cion'', 11 May 2002. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref name=\"MariaRita\">{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/maria-rita-kehl-velho-chico-reinaugura-um-desejo-de-utopia-20210647|title='Velho Chico' reinaugura um desejo de utopia|author=Maria Rita Kehl|date=1 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=O Brasil de Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 agreste. \u00c9 pobre, remediado, devastado e esperan\u00e7oso}}</ref> The baroque style<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diplomatique.org.br/uma-novela-shakespeareana-neorrealista-e-barroca/|title='Uma Novela Shakespearana, neorrealista e barroca|author=Helcio Kovaleski|date=15 March 2016|publisher=Le Monde Diplomatique Brasil|access-date=13 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Coelho\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1411200117.htm|title='Lavoura' e os ind\u00edcios de uma obra prima|author=Marcelo Coelho|date=14 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Lavoura Arcaica\" tem todas as raz\u00f5es para ser excessivo, barroco, quase ostentat\u00f3rio em sua riqueza estil\u00edstica. O filme consegue traduzir visualmente toda a beleza liter\u00e1ria do livro de Raduan Nassar}}</ref><ref name=\"Ilana\">{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/dois-irm%C3%A3os-arqueologia-da-mem%C3%B3ria-alegoria-da-destrui%C3%A7%C3%A3o-45b5723b88cd|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os: arqueologia da mem\u00f3ria, alegoria da destrui\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ilana Feldman|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Na obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o barroco \u00e9 um conceito norteador de uma pesquisa de linguagem: busca conceitual pela brasilidade presente nos opostos, nas contradi\u00e7\u00f5es e nos contrastes deste pa\u00eds}}</ref> of overlays and interlacing of narrative genres, the relation to the moment in Time,<ref name=\"Mata\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/critica/ult569u395.shtml|title=Em \"Lavoura Arcaica\", Carvalho faz retrato do tempo|author=Tiago Mata Machado|date=23 October 2001|publisher=FolhaOnline|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> the archetypal symbols of the Earth and the reflection on the language of social and family melodrama<ref name=\"Inacio\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1511200125.htm|title=Longa \u00e9 exce\u00e7\u00e3o exemplar no cinema do pa\u00eds|author=In\u00e1cio Ara\u00fajo|date=15 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> are features of the director's poetic language.\n\nThe filmmaker's works have met with both critical and public acclaim. He directed the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'' (2001)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://journals.openedition.org/cinelatino/2104|title=Du go\u00fbt du public selon Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Sylvie Debs|date=1 June 2008|publisher=Cin\u00e9mas d\u2019Am\u00e9rique latine|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/archives/article/2003/07/09/a-la-gauche-du-pere-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho_327204_1819218.html|title=\"A la gauche du p\u00e8re\", de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Florence Colombani|date=9 July 2003|publisher=Le Monde|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>, based on the homonymous novel by [[Raduan Nassar]], cited by the critic [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]] as a \"ground-breaking promise of renovation, of an upheaval not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]],<ref name=\"Cahiers\">Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.cineressources.net/articles_periodiques/resultat_f/index.php?pk=85803&param=F&textfield=a+la+gauche+du+pere&rech_type=F&rech_mode=exact&pageF=1&pageP=1&type=FOR&pk_recherche=85803 \" Les pieds dans la terre\"], ''Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma'', July\u2013August 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref><ref>Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/ \"On peut ais\u00e9ment voir dans cette grande fresque charnelle la plus belle d\u00e9couverte du cin\u00e9ma br\u00e9silien depuis Glauber Rocha, au moins parce que Luiz Fernando Carvalho partage avec le r\u00e9alisateur de Antonio das mortes un go\u00fbt pour la puissance du lyrisme\"], ''Chronicart'', 6 July 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref> which won over 50 national and international awards.<ref name=\"Montreal\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,montreal-premia-a-ousadia-de-lavoura-arcaica,20010905p2499 |title=Montreal premia a ousadia de \"Lavoura Arcaica\"|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=5 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The telenovelas ''[[Renascer|Renascer (Rebirth)]]'' (1993) and ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' (1996), by screenwriter [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, are recognized as benchmarks of Brazilian television drama and achieved some of the highest audience ratings of the 1990s.<ref>Hopewell, John [https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/rodrigo-santoro-globo-velho-chico-1201725234/ \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho (\u2018The King of the Cattle\u2019) returns with a rural romantic saga packing political overtones\"], ''Variety'', 8 March 2016. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv-pesquisa.com.puc-rio.br/mostraregistro.asp?CodRegistro=23342&PageNo=25|title=Renascer deu aula de dire\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|date=6 November 1993|publisher=Jornal do Brasil|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nThere is a marked contrast between the director's television works: from the pop design of the 60s in the series ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' (2013) to the classic rigor of the mini-series ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]'' (2001), the urban references of the working-class suburbs in the mini-series ''[[:pt:Suburbia|Suburbia]]'' (2012) to the playfulness of the soap ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' (2014), the aesthetic research of the Sert\u00e3o (backcountry) in ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' (2016) to the Brazilian fairytale of the mini-series ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005) and the realistic universe of family tragedy in ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' (2017).<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt \"Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu\"], ''University of Virginia'', 2014. Retrieved on 18 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660| title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction| journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies| volume=23| issue=4| pages=363\u2013379| year=2014| last1=Carter| first1=Eli Lee}}</ref>\n\nThe director's production process is renowned for identifying new talent from all over Brazil and for training actors,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,freud-explica,635078|title=Freu Explica|author=Patricia Vilalba|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=11 November 2010|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Freud explica: \"O processo de ensaios para filmar com Luiz Fernando \u00e9 um dos diferenciais do diretor, que o p\u00f4s em posi\u00e7\u00e3o de sonho de consumo de qualquer ator comprometido com seu of\u00edcio\"}}</ref> revealing new stars of the dramatic arts such as [[Leticia Sabatella]], [[Eliane Giardini]], [[Bruna Linzmeyer]], Johnny Massaro, [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Marcello Antony]], Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]], [[Giselle Iti\u00e9]], Emilio Orciollo Netto, Sheron Menezes, Jackson Antunes, [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], [[Eduardo Moscovis]], Jackson Costa, [[Leonardo Vieira]], Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Luciana Braga, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es, Cyria Coentro, Marina Nery, J\u00falio Machado, B\u00e1rbara Reis, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro and Lucy Alves, among others. The director's actor coaching technique has given rise to a method recounted in the book ''O processo de cria\u00e7\u00e3o dos atores de Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (''The creation process of the actors in Dois Irm\u00e3os''), by the photographer Leandro Pagliaro.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/tv/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-livro-registra-cenas-da-preparacao-do-elenco-da-minisserie-9303834.html/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": livro registra cenas da prepara\u00e7\u00e3o do elenco da miniss\u00e9rie|author=Roger Lerina|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/literatura,fotografo-registra-o-intenso-processo-de-ensaio-da-serie-dois-irmaos,10000098867|title=Fot\u00f3grafo registra o intenso processo de ensaio da s\u00e9rie 'Dois Irm\u00e3os'|author=Ubiratan Brasil|date=9 January 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box|width=40%|align=right|quote=\"There is a concrete promise of renovation, of a palpitation not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]]. (...) At first, one is left with nothing but fragments torn from a visual magma. But soon the chaos resolves itself, the film unrolls in all its richness like a barbaric poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power. (...) Never, however, does its return to the underlying myths obscure or accelerate the predominance of the sensations. If the film is possessed of such enchanting force, it is because Luiz Fernando Carvalho knows that everything starts there, in this first way of being born into the world, of allowing oneself to be ravished by it, to savor every twist of it...\"|source=\u2014Les Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma, by [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] on his critic about ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''<ref name=\"Cahiers\"/>}}\n\n== Early Career: 1980s ==\nLuiz Fernando Carvalho studied architecture and literature. He started out in cinema at 18 in a number of roles: audio technician, assistant director, screenwriter, short film editor and director. His first TV work came in the early 80s, as assistant director of noteworthy mini-series, such as ''[[O Tempo e o Vento]]'', based on the work of [[\u00c9rico Ver\u00edssimo]], directed by [[Paulo Jos\u00e9]], and ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'', from the work of [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa|Jo\u00e3o Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]], in which he started to direct his first scenes, still as assistant director to Walter Avancini.\n\n=== ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' ===\nHe wrote and directed the short ''The Waiting (A Espera)'', based on the book ''[[A Lover's Discourse: Fragments]]'' (''Fragments d'un discours amoureux'') by [[Roland Barthes]]. Launched in 1986, the film collected the following awards: Best Short Film, Best Actress ([[Marieta Severo]]) and Best Cinematography ([[Walter Carvalho]]) at the 13th [[Festival de Gramado]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|title=Lista de vencedores do Festival de Gramado de 1986|publisher=FestivaldeGramado.net|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104050/http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Best Short Film ([[Golden Shell]]) at the [[San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival]] (Spain); and the Special Jury Award at the Ste Ther\u00e8se Festival (Canada).\n\n== 1990s ==\n=== ''Sweet River (Riacho Doce)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nEarly in the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed a 40-chapter mini-series written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], based on the work of [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and starring [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]], Osmar Prado, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, [[Carlos Alberto Riccelli]] and [[Fernanda Montenegro]], with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The then inhospitable island of Fernando de Noronha (PE) served as the scene for the story, which is set in a small fishing village in the Northeast of Brazil.\n\n=== ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' ===\nIn 1991, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed an adaptation of a script by Brazilian TV pioneer P\u00e9ricles Leal, with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The telefilm was shot in the town of Canind\u00e9, Cear\u00e1, and reached the finals of the 34th [[New York Television Festival]]. This marked the television debut of actress [[Leticia Sabatella]]. The critic Rodrigo Fonseca affirmed that his first memory of Let\u00edcia Sabatella on TV was also when he discovered the existence of the \"genius of direction that is Luiz Fernando\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mulheresdocinemabrasileiro.com.br/site/entrevistas_depoimentos/visualiza/164/Rodrigo-Fonseca-Leticia-Sabatella|title=Let\u00edcia Sabatella, por Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=Mulheres do Cinema Brasileiro|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Foi quando eu tomei contato com a exist\u00eancia desse g\u00eanio da dire\u00e7\u00e3o que \u00e9 o Luiz Fernando}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Stone on Stone (Pedra Sobre Pedra)'' ===\n{{Main|Pedra Sobre Pedra}}\nIn 1992, he directed the telenovela written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], considered to have reached the 6th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\">{{cite web|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0,,EMI63532-9531,00.html |title=Aguinaldo Silva divulga lista das novelas com maior audi\u00eancia da hist\u00f3ria |date=10 March 2009 |publisher=Revista Quem |access-date=14 April 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045233/http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0%2C%2CEMI63532-9531%2C00.html |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>  Notable cast members included: [[Lima Duarte]], [[Renata Sorrah]], Armando B\u00f3gus, [[Eva Wilma]], [[Paulo Betti]], [[Andr\u00e9a Beltr\u00e3o]], Pedro Paulo Rangel and [[Eduardo Moscovis]]. Certain characters are regarded as landmarks in TV drama: Sergio Cabeleira (Osmar Prado) and the photographer Jorge Tadeu ([[F\u00e1bio Jr.]]).\n\n=== ''The Tale of Our Lady of Light (O Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz)'' ===\nWhile filming [[Pedra sobre Pedra]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho came up with a significant sequence inspired by [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s  Armorial Movement (Movimento Armorial) . The enormous success of the sequence, confirmed by the record number of requests by viewers for a rerun, was decisive in transformation of the material into a telefilm, with additional scenes written by Braulio Tavares and interpreted by the actor and musician [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]]. It competed for the [[International Emmy Award]] in 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|title=Curiosidades do Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104038/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Rebirth (Renascer)'' ===\n{{Main|Renascer}}\nThe 1993 soap, written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, met with critical and public acclaim and was the most watched in the 90s and 4th in audience ratings in the history of Brazilian television.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was also shown in several other countries. As directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, it is regarded as among the symbols of renovation of the aesthetics of the genre in the 90s.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KkJNHsGCYFkC&pg=PA219&lpg=PA219 |last=Jacob de Souza |first=Maria Carmen |title=Telenovela e representa\u00e7\u00e3o social: Benedito Ruy Barbosa e a representa\u00e7\u00e3o do popular na novela Renascer|publisher=E-papers|year=2004 |page=219 |isbn=978-85-87922-90-8|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, um dos mais expressivos representantes contempor\u00e2neos dessa tend\u00eancia autoral da dire\u00e7\u00e3o de telenovela, fez de Renascer seu sucesso mais exemplar}}</ref> The character Buba, interpreted by [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], caused a national controversy, as it was the first time that the discussion of gender had been addressed in a telenovela. It received the APCA Award for Best Novela, Best Actor ([[Antonio Fagundes]]), Best Supporting Actor (Osmar Prado), Best Supporting Actress (Regina Dourado), Best Male Breakthrough Performance (Jackson Antunes).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/6/02/ilustrada/21.html/|title=\"Renascer\" domina premia\u00e7\u00e3o de cr\u00edticos|author=Ana Beatriz Brisola|date=2 June 1994|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> [[Leonardo Vieira]], Jackson Antunes, Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]] and [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]] were among the talents revealed in this work. The television entrepreneur [[:pt:Boni|Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira]], considered the plot \"well structured by Benedito, with a well-crafted first part, masterfully directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Oliveira |first=Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio |date=2011 |title=O Livro do Boni |language=pt |location=S\u00e3o Paulo |publisher=Casa da Palavra |isbn=978-85-7734-226-6}}</ref> According to Marilia Martins, few novelas had a first chapter directed with such polish and skill as ''Rebirth''.\n\n=== ''A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol}}\nIn 1994, the telefilm directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho marked the first appearance of [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s works on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/3/09/ilustrada/2.html|title=Ariano Suassuna prepara estr\u00e9ia na TV|author=Marcelo Migliaccio|date=9 March 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=10 April 2017}}</ref> Based on the writer's unpublished novel of the same name, the script was the work of Ariano himself, in partnership with the director. Director of photography Dib Lufti, costumes by Luciana Buarque and art production by Lia Renha. Scenography by the artist Fernando Velloso, from the [[Grupo Corpo]] dance group, music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira, a member of the Armorial Quintet (Quinteto Armorial). With ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', the director commenced his exploration of the limits of television language, combining elements of the popular theater of the Northeast. Luiz Carlos Vasconcelos's Grupo Piolim participated and the cast included Tereza Seiblitz, Lineu Dias, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, Ana L\u00facia Torre, [[Raul Cortez]] and the then novice actor Floriano Peixoto. According to the researcher of Literature H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es, the work gave rise to an impasse at the TV station: was Lu\u00edz Fernando Carvalho too big for the Globo screen?<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/7/14/ilustrada/9.html|title=\"Mulher Vestida de Sol\" desafia o padr\u00e3o de realismo da Globo|author=H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es|date=14 July 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)}}\nOne year after ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', in 1995, Luiz Fernando Carvalho resumed his connection with the writer [[Ariano Suassuna]], this time transforming the play ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]'' into a telefilm . The director continued his search for a hybrid language for television, as a way of criticizing the naturalism of the novelas. Art production and costumes by Yurika Yamasaki and the artist Dantas Suassuna, participation of [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]], [[Patr\u00edcia Fran\u00e7a]], [[Ary Fontoura]] and [[Marieta Severo]]. According to the critic Rog\u00e9rio Durst, the telefilm was a major feat of TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=artigo&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=A+Farsa+da+Boa+Pregui%C3%A7a&anyword=&noword=&exactword=sofisticada&decadaSelecionada=1990&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title= Uma sofisticada op\u00e7\u00e3o popular|author=Rog\u00e9rio Durst|publisher=O Globo|date= 7 December 1995|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)'' ===\n{{Main Article|O Rei do Gado}}\n''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', 1996, the director's next collaboration with the author [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/novela-de-forte-cunho-social-rei-do-gado-de-benedito-ruy-barbosa-volta-ao-ar-nesta-segunda-15009118|title= Novela de forte cunho social, 'O rei do gado', de Benedito Ruy Barbosa, volta ao ar nesta segunda|author=Nat\u00e1lia Borde |publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=12 January 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> became the novela with the 9th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was rescreened three times,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/19/diretor-explica-por-que-terceira-reprise-de-rei-do-gado-faz-tanto-sucesso/|title=Diretor explica por que terceira reprise de \"Rei do Gado\" faz tanto sucesso|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=19 February 2015|publisher=UOL|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2015/02/1582950-reprise-de-o-rei-do-gado-chega-a-bater-novelas-ineditas-em-audiencia.shtml|title=Reprise de 'O Rei do Gado' chega a bater novelas in\u00e9ditas em audi\u00eancia|author=Fernanda Reis|date=1 February 2015|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> outrating other productions of the time, and was sold to over 30 countries. It marked the debut of [[Marcello Antony]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Mariana Lima]], Emilio Orciollo Netto and [[Lav\u00ednia Vlasak]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1996/10/20/revista_da_folha/3.html|title= Vidas com rumo|publisher=Revista da Folha|date=20 October 1996|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  Other significant aspects of the novela were its social criticism and sensitive approach to the Landless Workers Movement (movimento dos sem-terra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/direto-da-fonte/a-televisao-brasileira-tem-dado-claros-sinais-de-esgotamento-de-seu-modelo/|title=A televis\u00e3o brasileira tem dado claros sinais de esgotamento de seu modelo|author=Thais Arbex|date=16 December 2013|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote= Rei do Gado foi a primeira novela a abordar o conflito dos sem-terra e a reforma agr\u00e1ria}}</ref> The actors Jackson Antunes and [[Ana Beatriz Nogueira]] stand out in this context. The cast included [[Antonio Fagundes]], [[Patricia Pillar]], [[Leticia Spiller]] and [[Raul Cortez]] with guest appearances in the early stages by [[Tarcisio Meira]], [[Eva Wilma]] and [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]]. The character Ti\u00e3o Galinha, interpreted by Osmar Prado, is a landmark of his career. The novela received the Certificate of Merit at the [[San Francisco International Film Festival]] and the APCA Award for Best Actor ([[Raul Cortez]]), Best Supporting Actor (Leonardo Br\u00edcio), Best Supporting Actress (Walderez de Barros) and Best Male Breakthrough Performance ([[Caco Ciocler]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|title=Pr\u00eamios de'O Rei do Gado'|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328091627/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|archive-date=28 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernando de Barros e Silva wrote, in the Folha de S.Paulo, \"The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado) swallows up Brazilian cinema\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=O+Rei+do+Gado+engole+o+cinema+nacional+&site=&periodo=acervo&x=14&y=13|title=O Rei do Gado engole o cinema nacional |author=Fernando de Barros e Silva|date=7 July 1996|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to critic Rogerio Durst, the novela is \"a dramatic epic with first class special appearances and superb photography\".\n\nTiao Galinha belongs to another soap opera: \u201cRenascer\u201d.\n\n=== ''Giovanna and Henrico (Giovanna e Henrico)'' ===\nThe quality of the first seven chapters of ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', showing the decline of the coffee cycle and Brazil's participation in World War II, prompted The Globo Network's International Division to transform the first part of the novela into the mini-series ''Giovanna and Henrico'', with [[Let\u00edcia Spiller]] and Leonardo Br\u00edcio playing the lead couple. The production was selected as hors-concours at the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq150522.htm|title='O Rei do Gado' ganha pr\u00eamios em festivais|author=Cristina Padiglione|date=15 May 1997|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos}}\nBefore the end of the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho had already started on research for the feature film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''. Together with the author of the novel, [[Raduan Nassar]], he traveled to the Lebanon to familiarize himself with Mediterranean culture. The material collected during the trip was used to produce the documentary ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)]]'', screened on GNT in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1997/12/14/tv_folha/16.html |title='Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos' estr\u00e9ia no GNT|author=Mariana Scalzo|date=14 December 1997 |access-date=29 March 2017}}</ref> In the opinion of critic Rodrigo Fonseca, the documentary \"honed to the limit of tragic fatality its investigation of time\".\n\n== 2000s ==\n=== ''To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' ===\n{{Main Article|To the Left of the Father}}\nIn 2001, the director made his first feature film, ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', in which he was responsible for directing, screenplay and editing, with cinematography by Walter Carvalho, art direction by Yurika Yamazaki and costume design by Beth Filipecki.<ref name=\"Sukman\"/><ref name=\"Piza\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|title=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho vence o desafio de levar a literatura de Raduan Nassar para o cinema|author=Almir de Freitas|publisher=Revista Bravo!|access-date=17 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170418082444/http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|archive-date=18 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The cast included [[Selton Mello]], [[Raul Cortez]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Leonardo Medeiros]], [[Caio Blat]] and [[Juliana Carneiro da Cunha]]. Aiming to maintain the connection with the poetic prose of [[Raduan Nassar]]'s book, the director elected to film without a defined script, based entirely on the actors' improvisations on the theme.<ref name=\"Mata\"/><ref name=\"Coelho\"/><ref name=\"Inacio\"/> This involved intensive coaching of the cast, secluded on a farm for four months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1408200518.htm|title=Mergulho em Raduan Nassar conduz a pequena obra-prima|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|date=14 August 2005|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The film's creation and production process was discussed in the book ''About To the Left of The Father'' (\"Sobre Lavoura Arcaica\"), in which the director is interviewed by Jos\u00e9 Carlos Avellar, Geraldo Sarno, Miguel Pereira, Ivana Bentes, Arnaldo Carrilho and Liliane Heynemann, launched in Portuguese, English and French by the publisher [[:pt:Ateli\u00ea Editorial|Ateli\u00ea Editorial]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title= Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho |publisher=Atelier Cultural |year=2002|isbn=978-85-7480-140-7|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It was success with the critics<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=Lavoura+Arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=colheita&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2001&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Uma colheita espl\u00eandida|author=Luciano Trigo|publisher=RioShow|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=Filme+radicaliza+linguagem&site=&periodo=acervo&x=22&y=15|title=Filme radicaliza linguagem|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|publisher=Ilustrada/Folha de S.Paulo|date=24 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20011125-39485-spo-151-cd2-d3-not/busca/Lavoura+Arcaica|title=Convuls\u00f5es|author=Daniel Piza|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil|author=Diego Batle|publisher=La Nacion|language=spanish|date=11 May 2002|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and the public, reaching 300 thousand viewers with just two copies, one in Rio de Janeiro and the other in S\u00e3o Paulo. It is considered one of the [[Abraccine Top 100 Brazilian films|100 best Brazilian films of all times]], according to the Brazilian Film Critics Association (Abraccine).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://abraccine.org/2015/11/27/abraccine-organiza-ranking-dos-100-melhores-filmes-brasileiros/ |title= Abraccine organiza ranking dos 100 melhores filmes brasileiros |access-date= 26 October 2016 |author= Andr\u00e9 Dib |date= 27 November 2015 |publisher= abraccine.org}}</ref> It had a successful career in a number of national and international festivals, receiving over 50 awards at the [[Montreal World Film Festival]],<ref name=\"Montreal\"/><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.ffm-montreal.org/en/awards/16-awards-of-the-montreal-world-film-festival-2001.html/|title = 16 Awards of the Montreal World Film Festival 2001|website=FFMMontreal.org|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=n.d.|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Rio Film Festival]], the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]], the [[Grande Pr\u00eamio do Cinema Brasileiro|Grand Prix for Brazilian Film]], the [[Bras\u00edlia Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq2911200111.htm|title = Bras\u00edlia celebra \"Lavoura\" e \"Samba\"|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=29 November 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Havana Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1512200135.htm|title = \"Lavoura\" ganha pr\u00eamios em Havana|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=15 December 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Cartagena Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1103200214.htm|title = \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha Festival de Cartagena|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=11 March 2002|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Guadalajara International Film Festival]], the [[Buenos Aires International Festival of Independent Cinema]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pagina12.com.ar/diario/espectaculos/6-4799-2002-05-06.html|title=Una met\u00e1fora sobre los que no tienen lugar en la mesa social|author=Ana Bianco|language=spanish|publisher=P\u00e1gina 12|date=1 May 2002|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> among others. In the opinion of writer and psychoanalyst Renato Tardivo, author of ''Porvir que vem antes de tudo \u2013 literatura e cinema em Lavoura Arcaica'', the film is one of the most important works of Brazilian cinema \u201cof all times\u201d.<ref>{{cite book |last=Tardivo |first=Renato Cury  |title=Porvir que vem antes de tudo: uma leitura de lavoura arcaica - literatura, cinema e a unidade dos sentidos |publisher=Universidade de S\u00e3o Paulo (USP)|date=2009 |url= http://www.teses.usp.br/teses/disponiveis/47/47134/tde-11122009-110032/pt-br.php}}</ref> The critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos described it as the first work of art of the Brazilian cinema in the 21st century.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2016/10/13/festival-do-rio-lavoura-arcaica/|title=Festival do Rio: Lavoura Arcaica|author=Carlos Alberto de Mattos|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The film was acclaimed by the critics of various countries and, according to the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], ''To the Left of the Father'' is a \"barbarous poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/|title=Critique:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|author=Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|language=French|publisher=Chronicart|date=6 July 2003|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\">{{cite web| url=http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html|title=Critiques:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|publisher=AlloCin\u00e9|language=French|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\"/><ref>{{cite web| url=http://next.liberation.fr/cinema/2003/07/09/pere-de-tous-les-vices_439245|title=P\u00e9re de touts les vices. Relecture saisissante d'un monstre de la litt\u00e9rature br\u00e9silienne|author=Didier Peron|language=French|date=9 July 2003|publisher=Liber\u00e1cion|access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Maias (Os Maias)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nA 2001 production, this mini-series based on the homonymous novel by [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]] and adapted by Maria Adelaide Amaral was another landmark in the director's career.<ref>Elena Corr\u00eaa, \"Linguagem po\u00e9tica que remete a outra \u00e9poca. Roteiro fiel e dire\u00e7\u00e3o inconfund\u00edvel\", em \"O Globo\" (11 de janeiro de 2001)</ref> The Maias portrays the decadent Portuguese aristocracy in the second half of the 19th century, through the tragic story of a traditional Lisbon family. Costumes by Beth Filipecki and direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro. In the opinion of writer [[Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo]], \"the extraordinarily mobile camera of Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u201cvisited\u201d, more than portrayed, the frivolous Lisbon of the time and all the novel's atmospheres. But beneath it all, there was this majestic progression, from the first scene to the denouement, the moving camera conducting us like a slow tragic theme tune that recalls a symphony. No TV camera has ever been so complicit and seductive, never has TV been so romantic\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Wajnman |first=Solange  |title=Miniss\u00e9ries hist\u00f3ricas e a comunica\u00e7\u00e3o por objetos. Notas sobre os figurinos e cen\u00e1rios de 'Primo Bas\u00edlio' e \"Os Maias\"  |publisher=Universidade de Santa Maria (UFSM)|date=2011|url= https://periodicos.ufsm.br/animus/article/viewFile/4125/2624}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observatoriodaimprensa.com.br/artigos/qtv31012001991.htm|title=Os Maias|author=Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo|date=26 January 2001|publisher=Observat\u00f3riodaImprensa.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Para Os Maias, Carvalho escolheu um andamento que, na m\u00fasica, seria chamado de \u2018andante majestoso\u2019, que pode impacientar a gera\u00e7\u00e3o videoclipe, mas est\u00e1 perfeito, e era o ritmo preferido de Lean e Visconti.}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)'' ===\n{{Main|Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria}}\nOver two seasons, ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005), a mini-series in which he was also responsible for creation and script, consolidated the director's linguistic research.<ref>\"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria - segunda jornada \u00e9 uma joia lapidada com meticulosidade por um artista barroco, que n\u00e3o tem medo de abra\u00e7ar o excesso de refer\u00eancias universais e regionais para recriar a realidade brasileira com rigor e paix\u00e3o\", in \"Correio Braziliense\" (15 October 2005)</ref>  His co-writers were Luis Alberto de Abreu and Carlos Alberto Soffredini, basing themselves on a selection of stories taken from popular Brazilian oral storytelling tradition,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0901200511.htm|title=Carvalho invoca a cultura popular em micross\u00e9rie|author=Valmir Santos|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=9 January 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"\"Diretor associa \"Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria\" a uma busca pela identidade brasileira\"}}</ref> collected by the writers [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]], [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]] and [[Silvio Romero]]. Art direction by Lia Renha, guest artist Raimundo Rodriguez, direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro and costumes by Luciana Buarque. The 60 marionettes that represented the animals were produced by the Grupo Giramundo, from Minas Gerais state. The work marked the start of the partnership between the director and psychoanalyst Carlos Byington, as advisor on the mythological dramatization of the text. The mini-series was conceived under a 360\u00ba dome, scrap from a rock show stage. The sound track, by Tim Rescala, was based on cirandas (traditional dances) by [[Heitor Villa-Lobos]], [[C\u00e9sar Guerra-Peixe]] and [[Francisco Mignone]]. Designer Jum Nakao was responsible for some of the costumes, with animation of the stop-motion scenes by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]]. It received the 2005 APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critics' Choice Award, the ABC Best Photography Award, the Contigo Award for Best Director and Best Child Actress and the Brazil Quality Award (Pr\u00eamio Qualidade Brasil ) for Best Director, Television \u2013 Best Special Project, Best Author and Best Breakthrough Actress, and reached the finals of the 2005 [[International Emmy Award]], in the categories Best Mini-Series and Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u54506.shtml|title=Atriz mirim de \"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria\" \u00e9 indicada ao Emmy\"|publisher=Folha Online|date=21 October 2005|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> It was nominated Hors Concours by the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada (2006), and the [[International Public Television Screening Conference|Input International Board Taipei]] (2005). Compared with ''To the Left of the Father'' on account of its innovative television language, it caught the attention of critics and public by its novel, theatrical and playful language in transporting the universe of popular culture to a sophisticated television production, without losing its authenticity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+maria&anyword=&noword=&exactword=&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2005&mesSelecionado=10&revistaoglobo=on|title= Em Busca da nossa inf\u00e2ncia brasileira|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista OGlobo|date=9 October 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=As imagens de Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria s\u00e3o raras. Tudo escapa ao padr\u00e3o global: \u00e9 fic\u00e7\u00e3o que tem coragem de se revelar como fic\u00e7\u00e3o, \u00e9 uma TV que tem a ousadia de buscar nas origens do cinema a reinven\u00e7\u00e3o da linguagem}}</ref> The critic Nilson Xavier considers it one of the most poetic, original and beautiful productions of recent years.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.teledramaturgia.com.br/hoje-e-dia-de-maria/ |title=Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=Site Teledramaturgia |access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9, in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], the mini-series was very ambitious and formally very well produced, following other noteworthy projects such as ''The Maias (Os Maias)''.\n\n=== ''Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:A Pedra do Reino}}\nIn 2007, the director's third production based on the works of [[Ariano Suassuna]] brought to the TV the ''Romance d'A Pedra do Reino e o Pr\u00edncipe do Sangue do Vai-e-Volta''. The mini-series is regarded as yet another aesthetic innovation by the director, as in ''To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' and ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)''. The script was the work of Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in collaboration with Luis Alberto de Abreu and Braulio Tavares, direction of photography by Adrian Teijido, scenography by Jo\u00e3o Irenio Maia, editing by Marcio Hashimoto and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. Regional artists, coordinated by the artist Raimundo Rodriguez, assisted with the art production. Music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira (Quinteto Armorial) and Marco Ant\u00f4nio Guimar\u00e3es ([[Uakti (band)|Uakti]]). The cast was the fruit of the director's extensive search for talent throughout the backcountry (sert\u00e3o) of the Northeast. Television debut of the actors [[Irandhir Santos]] and Mayana Neiva and the singer Renata Rosa, among many others. It was filmed in the town of Tapero\u00e1, where [[Ariano Suassuna]] spent his childhood. During the coaching process, the team and cast attended lectures, out in the sert\u00e3o, by the actress [[Fernanda Montenegro]], the psychoanalyst Carlos Byington and the writer himself. [[Ariano Suassuna]] affirmed that Luiz Fernando Carvalho's recreation of his ''Romance d\u2019A Pedra do Reino'' resulted in an \"extraordinarily beautiful work that moved him as author and individual, as a spectator\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.revistacinetica.com.br/pedradoreinoilana.htm|title=A Pedra do Reino:A opera mundi de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Ilana Felman|publisher=Revista Cin\u00e9tica|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://ricardocalil.ig.com.br/index.php/2007/06/06/triunfo-da-imaginao/comment-page-1|title=Triunfo da Imagina\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ricardo Calil|publisher=iG |date=6 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=A Pedra do Reino segue mesmo a l\u00f3gica dos sonhos, com del\u00edrios visuais de intenso brilho e elipses de tempo, com desorienta\u00e7\u00f5es espaciais e suspens\u00f5es de sentido}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/leia-critica-da-microsserie-pedra-do-reino-4182728|title=cr\u00edtica da micross\u00e9rie 'A Pedra do Reino|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=\u201cA Pedra do Reino\u201d eleva \u00e0 en\u00e9sima pot\u00eancia um questionamento autoral onipresente nas hist\u00f3rias de Carvalho desde que rodou \u201cOs homens querem paz\u201d, um especial, exibido em 1991}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/24/diretor-de-a-pedra-do-reino-adaptara-fernando-e-isaura-para-a-tv.amp.htm|title=Diretor de \"A Pedra do Reino\" adaptar\u00e1 \"Fernando e Isaura\" para a TV|author=Andr\u00e9ia Rocha|publisher=UOL|date=24 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/11/1934597-editora-lanca-dois-volumes-de-obra-postuma-de-ariano-suassuna.shtml|title=Nova Fronteira lan\u00e7a dois volumes de obra p\u00f3stuma de Ariano Suassuna|author=Claudio Leal |date=11 November 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Portando nomes reais ou acrescidos de sobrenomes ficcionais, amigos surgem em ep\u00edgrafes e s\u00e3o incorporados pelo escritor como personagens dos di\u00e1logos sobre a cultura brasileira e seu projeto liter\u00e1rio. As atrizes Inez Viana e Marieta Severo , os diretores Aderbal Freire Filho e Luiz Fernando Carvalho, os poetas Jos\u00e9 Laurenio de Melo e Ad\u00e9lia Prado se situam entre esses interlocutores de Dom Pantero na \"Autobiografia Musical, Dan\u00e7arina, Po\u00e9tica, Teatral e V\u00eddeo-CinematoGr\u00e1fica\"}}</ref>\n\n=== Quadrante Project (Projeto Quadrante) ===\nBased on ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]'' (2007), the director set up the Quadrante Project with the intention of making a series of regional drama programs to rediscover the Brazilian imaginary through adaptations of literary texts of authors from each Brazilian state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1712200617.htm|title=Sert\u00e3o \u00e9 \"semente\" de \"A Pedra do Reino\"|author=Esther Hamburguer|publisher=Revista Cult|date=17 December 2006|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> Similarly, local actors act out the texts. The richness of the project lay in the discovery of regional talent: authors, actors, composers, artists in general. The project recognized the human potential of each regional culture, looking beyond the simplistic image of a postcard. In addition to ''Stone of the Kingdom'', the Quadrante is made up of the mini-series [[Capitu]] (2008), based on the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]], and ''Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (2017), by [[Milton Hatoum]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/dois-irmaos-retoma-antigo-projeto-artistico-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-e-tem-primeiro-capitulo-deslumbrante|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os retoma antigo projeto art\u00edstico de Luiz Fernando Carvalho e tem primeiro cap\u00edtulo deslumbrante|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio da Televis\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Capitu'' ===\n{{Main|Capitu}}\nIn 2008, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed and finalized the script for this adaptation of the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu  |publisher=University of Virginia|date=2014|url= http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt}}</ref> The mini-series was written by Euclydes Marinho in collaboration with Daniel Piza, Luis Alberto de Abreu and Edna Palatnik. Art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez, photography by Adrian Teijido and costumes by Beth Filipecki. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. It marked the TV debut of actors [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]] and Michel Melamed, among others. The mini-series was filmed in the abandoned Autom\u00f3vel Clube building, in downtown Rio de Janeiro, and the whole scenographic universe was created from newspaper and recycled material. The opening credits scene was conceived by the director and created by the designer Carlos B\u00eala.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/2475349/|title=Abertura de Capitu|author=Carlos B\u00eala|publisher=Vimeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The production is part of the Quadrante Project and was the director's tribute to [[Machado de Assis]] on the centenary of his death. It received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critic's Choice Award (2009), ABC Best Photography Award  (from the Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) and the [[Creative Review]] award in the Best in Book and Design and Art Director categories. In the opinion of critic Gustavo Bernardo, the mini-series deserves \"to be viewed and reviewed countless times, at least because each fragment of a scene is precious for its beauty\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-capitu-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-145085.html|title=A Capitu de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Gustavo Bernardo|publisher=O Globo|date=9 December 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to theatre director [[:pt:Gabriel Villela|Gabriel Villela]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho produces works of art on the screen, calls on the viewer's vivacity so that he accepts nothing masticated, but masticates along with Casmurro.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0808200923.htm|title=\"Capitu\" traduz para TV modo de narrar de Machado de Assis|author=Gabriel Villela|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=8 August 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> For Randall Johnson, director of the UCLA Latin American Institute, \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho is today, without doubt, the director whose work is the most authorial of all TV and cinema production in Brazil\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/curso-na-universidade-da-california-debate-obra-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-3144586|title=Curso na Universidade da Calif\u00f3rnia debate obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=24 May 2009|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://renatofelix.wordpress.com/2009/08/27/entrevistas-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Entrevistas: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Renato Felix|publisher=Blog do Renato Felix|date=27 August 2009|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Trata-se um ensaio sobre a d\u00favida. N\u00e3o absolvo Capitu e n\u00e3o a condeno}}</ref>\n\n== 2010s ==\n\n=== ''After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?}}\nIn 2010, Luiz Fernando Carvalho created, directed and wrote the mini-series inspired by [[Sigmund Freud]]'s: famous question \"What does a woman want?\". [[Jo\u00e3o Paulo Cuenca]], Cecilia Giannetti and [[:pt:Michel Melamed|Michel Melamed]] collaborated on the script. As well as acting in the production, Melamed created the opening sound track. Direction of Photography Adrian Teijido, costumes by Beth Filipecki and art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez. The director launched actress [[Bruna Linzmeyer]]\u2019s career in this production. Osmar Prado shared the part of Freud with a model animated by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]], using the stop-motion technique.  The opening vignette features the work of German artist [[Olaf Hajek]], who also produced special illustrations for the mini-series by invitation of the director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/17214632|title=Abertura da miniss\u00e9rie \"Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?\"|author=Alexandre Romano|publisher=V\u00edmeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It received the ABC award (Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) for Best Photography. According to columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, \"it is an oneiric journey, a visual poem that blends realities, full of references to times past, to what has been experienced, to what lingers in memory\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2010/11/critica-afinal-que-querem-as-mulheres-340331.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=13 November 2010|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction |journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies |volume=23 |issue=4 |pages=363\u2013379 |date=2014|doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660 }}</ref>\n\n=== ''Suburbia'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Suburbia}}\nIn 2012, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated in TV drama a production in which all the protagonists are of African descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/critica/2012/11/01/seriado-olha-com-realismo-mas-carinho-para-a-dura-vida-no-suburbio.htm|title=Seriado olha com realismo, mas carinho para a dura vida no sub\u00farbio|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/suburbia-uma-entrevista-com-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Suburbia: uma entrevista com Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Luiz Zanin|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=3 November 2012|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The mini-series, created and written by the director in partnership with Paulo Lins, counted on the collaboration of Adrian Teijido (Photography), Luciana Buarque (Costumes), Marcio Hashimoto (Editing) and Sergio Pasqualino (Colorist). It also marked the start of another research cycle, in which the director focused on realist aesthetics, which influenced the language as a whole, but mainly in the choice of non-actors for the main parts. The nearly 40 actors launched in the mini-series include artists of the groups N\u00f3s do Morro and [[:pt:Afroreggae|Afroreggae]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2012/12/critica-naturalidade-e-ausencia-de-pose-o-mundo-de-suburbia.html|title=Naturalidade e aus\u00eancia de pose: o mundo de 'Suburbia'|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=3 December 2012|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> \u00c9rika Januza, until then secretary of a school in the interior of Minas Gerais state, was chosen to play the main character of the story. Guest appearance by Fabr\u00edcio Boliveira, Rosa Marya Colin, Haroldo Costa, Maria Salvadora, Paulo Tiefenthaler and Dani Ornellas, among others. In 2012, the Globo network took the series up again for a second season in 2013 due to its satisfactory audience ratings. Later, however, the director Luiz Fernando Carvalho chose to cancel the new season. In the opinion of anthropologist Luiz Eduardo Soares, the work was a \"reconstructive reading of the carioca society, producing a superb result \".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-eduardo-soares-escreve-sobre-intensidade-da-forma-em-suburbia-6733970|title=Luiz Eduardo Soares escreve sobre a intensidade da forma em 'Suburbia'|author=Luiz Eduardo Soares|publisher=O Globo|date=15 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Ladie\u2019s Mail (Correio Feminino)''===\n{{Main|:pt:Correio Feminino}}\nA mini-series in eight episodes, created and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho based on women's journals written by [[Clarice Lispector]] in the 1950s and 1960s, under the pseudonym Helen Palmer. The visual language and narrative were based on 60s pop art and design,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/quero-um-novo-ciclo-na-tv-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho-10375021|title='Quero um novo ciclo na TV', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> from the costumes to the lighting and set; all filmed in a single light box, which changed color according to the subjects addressed. Adapted by Maria Camargo, the series was shown in 2013 as part of the program Fant\u00e1stico,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-fernando-carvalho-dirige-serie-correio-feminino-estreia-deste-domingo-do-fantastico-10543381|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho dirige s\u00e9rie Correio Feminino, estreia deste domingo do Fant\u00e1stico|author=Zean Bravo|publisher=O Globo|date=27 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> with costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie and Luciana Buarque, photography by Mikeas and edited by Marcio Hashimoto. The actress [[Maria Fernanda C\u00e2ndido]] played Helen Palmer narrating all the episodes. In the cast, [[Luiza Brunet]] interpreted the mature woman, and [[:pt:Alessandra Maestrini|Alessandra Maestrini]], the young woman. The adolescent is [[Cintia Dicker]], an international model whose acting career was launched in the mini-series. In the opinion of critic Patricia Kogut, the series is \"inspired, pleasant, in good taste and unpretentious, like Clarice's texts as Helen Palmer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/11/correio-feminino-faz-leitura-inspirada-de-clarice-lispector.html|title='Correio feminino' faz leitura inspirada de Clarice Lispector|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=5 November 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Alexandre and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)}}\nA 2013 telefilm, with script by Luis Alberto de Abreu and Luiz Fernando Carvalho<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-consciencia-dos-sonhos-por-luiz-fernando-carvalho-518115.html|title=A consci\u00eancia dos sonhos - Diretor de 'Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is', especial de TV baseado nas hist\u00f3rias infantojuvenis de Graciliano Ramos, examina dimens\u00f5es m\u00edtica, ut\u00f3pica e humana na obra do alagoano|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho|publisher=OGlobo|date=14 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> based on two stories by the Alagoan writer [[Graciliano Ramos]]. Luiz Fernando Carvalho's coaching and directing of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation to [[Marcelo Serrado]] and [[Ney Latorraca]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atarde.uol.com.br/cultura/televisao/noticias/1555977-ney-latorraca-e-destaque-em-alexandre-e-outros-herois|title=Ney Latorraca \u00e9 destaque em 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|date=16 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=A Tarde|author=Roberta Pennafort}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2013/12/1383371-ney-latorraca-renasce-em-especial-na-tv-alexandre-e-outros-herois.shtml|title=Ney Latorraca renasce em especial na TV 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|author=Gislaine Gutierre|publisher=Folha Online|date=10 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Ele (Luiz Fernando Carvalho) me tirou totalmente da zona de conforto}}</ref> as well as a harmony in the quality of the interpretations. Direction of photography by Mickeas, art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Incidental sound track by Tim Rescala. Opening theme by the Pernambucan Siba. The cast of the TV special, a finalist in the 2014 [[International Emmy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/finalista-do-emmy-internacional-alexandre-outros-herois-pode-ter-mais-episodios-em-2015-14233742|title=Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is \u00e9 finalista do Emmy Internacional|date=14 October 2014|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Revista da TV|author=Nilton Carauta}}</ref> also included Fl\u00e1vio Bauraqui, Fl\u00e1vio Rocha, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and Luci Pereira.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/direcao-seca-faz-a-qualidade-tecnica-de-alexandre-e-outros-herois-1577#ixzz4dl00ba3T|title=Dire\u00e7\u00e3o 'seca' faz a qualidade t\u00e9cnica de Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is|date=19 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|author=Raphael Scire}}</ref> Critic Patricia Kogut considered the telefilm a miniature work of art on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/12/alexandre-e-outros-herois-uma-pequena-obra-prima-na-globo.html|title='Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is': uma pequena obra-prima na Globo|date=20 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|quote=Trata-se de uma viagem horizontal pela cultura popular, sem o olhar estrangeiro, ou a entroniza\u00e7\u00e3o daquilo que \u00e9 simples. Essa \u00e9 uma das maiores virtudes do programa adaptado por Lu\u00eds Alberto de Abreu e com a clar\u00edssima assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho. N\u00e3o vimos a alta cultura caindo na tenta\u00e7\u00e3o popularizante e sim uma produ\u00e7\u00e3o abertamente popular e ao mesmo tempo elegante e requintada, com ambi\u00e7\u00e3o art\u00edstica e dona de um universo est\u00e9tico pr\u00f3prio, original}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2013/12/25/luiz-fernando-carvalho-lembra-que-ha-lugar-para-graciliano-ramos-na-tv/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho lembra que h\u00e1 lugar para Graciliano Ramos na TV|author=Mauricio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=25 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)'' ===\n{{Main|Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o}}\nThis 2014 production marked the director's return to the telenovela format after 12 years of dedicating himself to mini-series and more authorial projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2014/04/1445086-luiz-fernando-carvalho-critica-novelas-tradicionais-e-cruza-conto-de-fadas-e-hq.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho critica novelas tradicionais e cruza conto de fadas e HQ|author=Sylvia Colombo|publisher=Serafina|date=27 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/31/e-preciso-renovar-mais-e-copiar-menos-diz-diretor-de-meu-pedacinho.htm|title=\u00c9 preciso renovar mais e copiar menos, diz diretor de Meu Pedacinho|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' was written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, with art production by Marco Cortez, art work by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. The critics praised various aspects, from the harmony of the quality of acting to the editing, direction, costumes, scenography and aesthetics, inspired by Westerns and Japanese manga (comics).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estetica-que-deu-certo-4564521.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o: A Est\u00e9tica que deu certo|author=Vanessa Scalei|publisher=Zero Hora|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2014/08/01/meu-pedacinho-do-chao-fugiu-do-obvio-surpreendeu-e-encantou/|title=Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o fugiu do \u00f3bvio e surpreendeu|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 August 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/cinco-motivos-para-tornar-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-inesquecivel-4268|title=Cinco motivos para tornar Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o inesquec\u00edvel|author=Raphael Scire|publisher=UOL|date=30 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/05/linda-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-dissolve-duvidas-da-estreia.html|title='Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o' dissolve d\u00favidas na estreia|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=27 May 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o \u00e9 uma das grandes produ\u00e7\u00f5es da nossa TV. Segue linda, artesanal dentro do poss\u00edvel e \u00e9 carregada principalmente por sua hist\u00f3ria. Dentro daquele ambiente on\u00edrico e l\u00edrico, h\u00e1 dramas e conflitos s\u00e9rios. Eles capturam a aten\u00e7\u00e3o do p\u00fablico com for\u00e7a. E a beleza dos cen\u00e1rios e figurinos n\u00e3o dissimula nem diminui esses recados}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,meu-pedacinho-de-chao-nao-se-acomoda-e-faz-nevar-no-rio,1531589|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o n\u00e3o se acomoda e faz nevar no Rio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=21 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Luiz Fernando Carvalho's direction of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation, noted by the critics, to actors such as [[Juliana Paes]] and [[Rodrigo Lombardi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/04/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estreia-com-marca-do-diretor.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor (...) Juliana Paes, madura, exuberante, respondeu bem \u00e0 m\u00e3o forte da dire\u00e7\u00e3o. Mostrou que avan\u00e7ou um passo na sua trajet\u00f3ria de atriz}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching to shape the aesthetics of ''My Little Plot of Land'' took place at TVLi\u00ea, known as Galp\u00e3o, which operated from 2013 to 2017. The space brought together all the creative teams and was conceived by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, at Projac, for collaborative project creation and talent training. In addition to ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'', the works ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Female Messages (Correio Feminino)]]'', ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexander and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'', ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' were created in the Galp\u00e3o. The whole process of creation and production of the novela in the Galp\u00e3o is described by the journalist Melina Dalboni in the book ''Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'', which has drawings, sketches and photos by the director and the team (published by Casa da Palavra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/13/livro-prolonga-a-experiencia-dos-fas-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao/|title=Livro prolonga experi\u00eancia dos f\u00e3s do Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=13 February 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Sets and costumes were envisaged through the playful eye of childhood,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/conheca-detalhes-da-criacao-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-trama-com-universo-onirico-ar-de-fabula-12586431|title=Conhe\u00e7a detalhes da cria\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Meu pedacinho de ch\u00e3o', trama com universo on\u00edrico e ar de f\u00e1bula|author=Nat\u00e1lia Castro|publisher=Revista da TV|date=26 June 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> and according to the columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, contributed to a beautiful invented universe, far different from what we are used to seeing on TV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-deixara-sua-marca-na-historia-da-televisao.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o deixar\u00e1 sua marca na hist\u00f3ria da TV|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The houses were faced with recycled cans, based on the work of artist Raimundo Rodriguez. The costumes, the subject of an exhibition, mixed technological fabrics and plastic material.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2014/12/exposicao-exibe-figurino-da-novela-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-no-rio.html|title=Exposi\u00e7\u00e3o exibe figurinos de Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o|publisher=G1|date=27 December 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Cesar Coelho, of the Anima Mundi Festival, used stop-motion and time-lapse techniques for all the animation. The novela received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]); Contigo Magazine Award for Best Child Actor (Tom\u00e1s Sampaio) and Best Director; the Extra television award  for Best Costumes and Best Makeup (Rubens Lib\u00f3rio); and the Quem Magazine award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]), Best Supporting Actor (Johnny Massaro) and Best Author ([[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]]). The critic Cristina Padiglione regards the novela as worthy of a standing ovation, and in the opinion of Alexandra Moraes \"the images, at first sight childish, gain relevance with colors and effects of dramatic intent. Good performances and the firm hand of the director give the plot meaning\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/cristina-padiglione/isso-nao-e-um-pedacinho-de-chao-e-um-latifundio/|title=Isso n\u00e3o \u00e9 um 'pedacinho' de ch\u00e3o, \u00e9 um latif\u00fandio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2014/04/1437903-critica-cores-e-filtros-reforcam-trama-em-meu-pedacinho-de-chao.shtml|title=Cr\u00edtica: Cores e filtros refor\u00e7am trama em 'Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'|author=Alexandra Moraes|publisher=Ilustrada - Folha de S.Paulo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Old River (Velho Chico)'' ===\n{{Main|Velho Chico (telenovela)}}\nIn 2016, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' marked Luiz Fernando Carvalho's return to prime time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/velho-chico-folhetim-classico-mas-com-muita-renovacao.html|title='Velho Chico': folhetim cl\u00e1ssico, mas com muita renova\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico, como outras obras de Carvalho, provou que a ind\u00fastria cultural da televis\u00e3o tamb\u00e9m pode ter ares de artesanato. N\u00e3o \u00e9 pouco\"}}</ref> directing the novela written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and Bruno Luperi, which again carried the imprint of the new esthetic in TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omelete.uol.com.br/series-tv/entrevista/velho-chico-stanley-kubrick-da-tv-brasileira-diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-novela/|title=\"Stanley Kubrick da TV brasileira\", diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a novela|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=14 March 2016|publisher=Omelete.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/01/1734731-a-maior-funcao-da-televisao-e-criar-cidadaos-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho.shtml|title='A maior fun\u00e7\u00e3o da televis\u00e3o \u00e9 criar cidad\u00e3os', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita|date=31 January 2016|publisher=Ilustrada|work=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=24 February 2016}}</ref> The novela was divided into two phases,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/06/velho-chico-tem-cenas-para-amarrar-o-presente-ao-passado.html |title='Velho Chico' tem cenas para amarrar o presente e o passado|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|date=15 June 2016|publisher=O Globo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> with direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. Highlights were the photography<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-fotografia-peculiar-da-novela-velho-chico,10000064739|title=Diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a fotografia peculiar da novela 'Velho Chico'|author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=25 July 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho e a fotografia viscontiana da novela \u2018Velho Chico\u2019}}</ref> and acclaimed performances by the actors [[Antonio Fagundes]], Lucy Alves, [[Domingos Montagner]], Lee Taylor, [[Marcos Palmeira]], [[Chico Diaz]], Renato G\u00f3es, [[Rodrigo Lombardi]], [[Dira Paes]], [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Fabiula Nascimento]], Julia Dalavia, Cyria Coentro, Barbara Reis, Julio Machado, Umberto Magnani, [[Camila Pitanga]], [[Christiane Torloni]], [[Marcelo Serrado]], Gabriel Leone, Giulia Buscaccio, Mariene de Castro, G\u00e9sio Amadeu, Jos\u00e9 Dumont, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2016/12/quem-fez-festa-dos-telespectadores-em-2016.html|title=Quem fez a festa dos telespectadores em 2016|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=29 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico trouxe um vento novo para a faixa das 21h (...) Entre os destaques desse elenco estiveram novatos e veteranos, numa mistura de atores que encantou o p\u00fablico. Domingos Montagner, tragicamente morto perto da loca\u00e7\u00e3o, impressionou mais uma vez, como o Santo. Marcos Palmeira esteve no melhor papel da sua carreira. Antonio Fagundes, depois de ajustes no personagem, fez um coronel grandioso. Chico Diaz, Lucy Alves, Fabiula Nascimento, Zezita Matos, Christiane Torloni, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es e tantos outros brilharam\"}}</ref> The cast was of a uniformity rarely seen in novelas, resulting in countless awards for its actors, including the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actress for Selma Egrei and the Critics' Choice Award for [[Domingos Montagner]](posthumous) and the production also won Best Supporting Actress (Selma Egrei), Best Supporting Actor (Irandhir Santos), Best Breakthrough Actress (Lucy Alves) and Best Breakthrough Actor (Lee Taylor),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/velho-chico-justica-selma-egrei-e-marco-ricca-sao-premiados-na-apc|title='Velho Chico', 'Justi\u00e7a', Selma Egrei e Marco Ricca s\u00e3o premiados na APCA|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Telepadi|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/11/1837325-aquarius-velho-chico-rita-lee-e-montagner-levam-premios-da-apca.shtml|title='Aquarius', 'Velho Chico', Rita Lee e Montagner levam pr\u00eamios da APCA|publisher=Folha Online|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> with Veja Rio's Carioca of the Year Award going to Luiz Fernando Carvalho for the renovated aesthetic of prime time television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vejario.abril.com.br/cidades/luiz-fernando-carvalho-cria-uma-nova-estetica-para-o-horario-nobre/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho cria uma nova est\u00e9tica para o hor\u00e1rio nobre|author=Sofia Cerqueira |publisher=Veja Rio|date=10 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching lasted only three months and took place at TVli\u00ea, Luiz Fernando Carvalho's collaborative creative space, which operated at Projac between 2013 and 2017 and was known as Galp\u00e3o.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amarello.com.br/artigo/amarello-visita-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Amarello Visita: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Tom\u00e1s Biagi Carvalho|publisher=Amarello|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Para preparar os atores de seus projetos, construiu um galp\u00e3o: uma mistura de circo com escola de samba, mambembe, feito de material reciclado e resto de cen\u00e1rio; uma c\u00e9lula criativa dentro dos Est\u00fadios Globo.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2016/03/1743767-atores-de-velho-chico-nova-novela-da-globo-fazem-experiencias-em-galpao.shtml|title=Atores de 'Velho Chico' fazem experi\u00eancias em galp\u00e3o|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita |publisher=Serafina|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Os personagens de todo o elenco da saga familiar escrita por Benedito Ruy Barbosa eram gestados em um espa\u00e7o coletivo de experimenta\u00e7\u00e3o idealizado pelo diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/lindo-capitulo-marca-volta-do-brasil-rural-21h.html|title=Lindo cap\u00edtulo marca a volta do Brasil rural \u00e0 TV|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=16 March 2016|quote=\"A estreia de ''Velho Chico'' teve mesmo o selo autoral do seu diretor, Luiz Fernando Carvalho.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/velho-chico-e-o-brasil-real-e-o-da-fantasia.html|title=Velho Chico e o Brasil real e o da fantasia|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=18 March 2016|quote=\"''Velho Chico'', de alguma forma, trouxe a f\u00e1bula de volta ao hor\u00e1rio nobre. (...) Mas a realiza\u00e7\u00e3o de Luiz Fernando Carvalho faz sonhar. E a hist\u00f3ria de Benedito Ruy Barbosa tem muitas chances de agradar com essa mistura de realidade \u00e1rida com estetiza\u00e7\u00e3o.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The first phase, applauded by the critics, marked the return of actor [[Rodrigo Santoro]] to the Globo fold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/rodrigo-santoro-volta-as-novelas-da-globo-17902522|title=Rodrigo Santoro volta \u00e0s novelas|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  and revealed the hitherto undiscovered talent of [[Carol Castro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/novelas/sensacao-de-velho-chico-carol-castro-teve-de-fazer-teste-chorando-10725 |title=Sensa\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico, Carol Castro teve de fazer teste chorando|author=Marcia Pereira|date=16 March 2016|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> [[Tarc\u00edsio Meira]], in just two episodes, put in an impressive performance, as did actress Selma Egrei, who took part in both phases of the novela.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.correio24horas.com.br/single-entretenimento/noticia/selma-egrei-se-destaca-em-velho-chico-com-a-sofrida-e-poderosa-encarnacao/?cHash=87ff234ae84127b9c7650a9a82598eae|title=Selma Egrei se destaca em 'Velho Chico' com a sofrida e poderosa Encarna\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Roberto Midlej |publisher=Correio Popular|date=7 August 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The cast was selected after an extensive  search for actors from the Northeast and marked the debut in novelas of Lucy Alves, Renato G\u00f3es, Marina Nery, Barbara Reis, Diyo Coelho, Xangai, Veronica Cavalcanti, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro, Yara Charry, Raiza Alc\u00e2ntara, Lucas Veloso, Sueli Bispo and the comedian Bator\u00e9.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-tera-60-do-elenco-composto-por-atores-nordestinos-18716574|title=Velho Chico' ter\u00e1 60% do elenco composto por atores nordestinos|author=Zean Bravo |publisher=Revista da TV|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-procura-atores-por-todo-o-pais-para-novela-das-9,1777455|title=Diretor procura atores por todo o pa\u00eds para a novela das 9|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The last chapters of the novela pay tribute to the actor [[Domingos Montagner]] (Santo), who drowned in the S\u00e3o Francisco river two weeks before the end of the serial. The character was maintained in the plot even after the actor's death through the language created by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in which a single subjective camera interpreted Santo's viewpoint, so his presence was felt, engaging with all the other characters, to the end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/camera-subjetiva-solucao-de-velho-chico-para-santo-e-linda/ |title=C\u00e2mera subjetiva: solu\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Velho Chico' para Santo \u00e9 linda|author=Marcia Carolina Maia|date=27 September 2016|publisher=Veja|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/obrigado-velho-chico/|title=Cr\u00edtica: Obrigado, \"Velho Chico\"|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=30 September 2016|publisher=UOL|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/presenca-incorporea-de-domingos-montagner-em-velho-chico.html|title=A Presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea de Domingos Montagner em Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=28 September 2016|quote=\"Nem dubl\u00ea, nem truques rasteiros. V\u00edtima de uma trag\u00e9dia que entristeceu o Brasil \u2014 e mais ainda a equipe de ''Velho Chico'' \u2014, Domingos Montagner estava na novela anteontem. Luiz Fernando Carvalho recorreu a uma c\u00e2mera subjetiva para trazer a presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea do ator a quase todas as sequ\u00eancias. Era, claro, um recurso t\u00e9cnico. Por\u00e9m, qualquer car\u00e1ter racional foi plenamente absorvido pela dramaturgia e dissolvido pela emo\u00e7\u00e3o vis\u00edvel que dominou o elenco e alcan\u00e7ou o p\u00fablico. (...) Carvalho chegou perto de fronteiras perigosas e acertou muito mesmo.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The novela came under strong pressure from the Globo network's drama department, calling for modifications to the text, storyline and esthetics. The director and the author, [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]], stood firm and refused to make the changes to ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]''. The in-house crisis made the TV columns and was described as a form of public pressure on Luiz Fernando Carvalho. According to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' is a landmark in the recent history of Brazilian TV, on account of its esthetic ambition and cultural relevance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2016/10/1818880-velho-chico-marcou-pela-ambicao-estetica-e-a-relevancia-cultural.shtml |title='Velho Chico' marcou pela ambi\u00e7\u00e3o est\u00e9tica e a relev\u00e2ncia cultural|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=1 October 2016|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Nilson Xavier, the novela \u201chad incontestable technical and artistic quality, from the direction to the photography, sound track and the actors\u2019 performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/o-maior-merito-de-velho-chico-foi-provocar-e-estimular-o-publico/|title=O maior m\u00e9rito de Velho Chico foi provocar e estimular o p\u00fablico|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=UOL|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u00c9 de Boni (Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira Sobrinho) a frase: \u201cA televis\u00e3o deve andar sempre um passo \u00e0 frente do p\u00fablico.\u201d \u201cVelho Chico\u201d foi um bom exemplo\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/telinha/critica-sobre-fim-de-velho-chico-tintas-fortes-do-inicio-ao-fim-20212649.html|title=Cr\u00edtica de Velho Chico: tintas fortes do in\u00edcio ao fim|author=Carla Bittencourt|publisher=Extra|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"Velho Chico\u201d sempre foi uma novela de atua\u00e7\u00f5es e cenas memor\u00e1veis (...). Tudo muito denso, pintado com tintas mais fortes do que o telespectador est\u00e1 acostumado a ver nesse hor\u00e1rio. Essas caracter\u00edsticas garantiram \u00e0 trama seu lugar na hist\u00f3ria da teledramaturgia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2016/09/final-de-velho-chico-emociona-com-brilhante-atuacao-de-antonio-fagundes|title=Final de Velho Chico emociona com brilhante atua\u00e7\u00e3o de Antonio Fagundes|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|title=Noveleiro|publisher=O Globo|author=Luis Fernando Verissimo|date=1 May 2016|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Eu j\u00e1 tentava ver tudo o que Luiz Fernando Carvalho fazia, e n\u00e3o apenas por solidariedade de xar\u00e1. O que ele est\u00e1 fazendo no ''Velho Chico'' ultrapassa tudo o que j\u00e1 fez na TV - com a poss\u00edvel exce\u00e7\u00e3o de ''Os Maias''. Ele \u00e9 incapaz de um enquadramento que n\u00e3o seja perfeito, e teve tamb\u00e9m o talento de escolher um elenco perfeito.\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201032703/http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> It competed for the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://upload.iemmys.tv/public/iemmys/Nominees.aspx?nc=I|title=Nominees Categories|publisher=Iemmys.tv|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/kenneth-branagh-anna-friel-international-emmy-nominations-1202574242/|title=Kenneth Branagh, Anna Friel Receive International Emmy Nominations|publisher=Variety|author=Stewart Clarke|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4854403/emmy-nominations-2017/|title=Here Are the 2017 Emmy Nominations|publisher=Time|author=Kate Samuelson |date=13 July 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-justica-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional-21876053|title=Velho Chico e Justi\u00e7a concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=Revista da TV,O Globo|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gshow.globo.com/programas/video-show/noticia/justica-ta-no-ar-velho-chico-totalmente-demais-e-alemao-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional.ghtml|title=Justi\u00e7a, T\u00e1 no ar, Velho Chico, Totalmente Demais e Alem\u00e3o concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=GShow|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/a-contradicao-de-velho-chico-novela-e-finalista-ao-emmy-mas-nao-cabe-no-catalogo-de-vendas-internacionais/|title=A contradi\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico: novela \u00e9 finalista ao Emmy mas n\u00e3o cabe no cat\u00e1logo de vendas internacionais|publisher=Telepadi|date=27 September 2017|quote=\u00c9 quase uma contradi\u00e7\u00e3o que o enredo n\u00e3o tenha apelo internacional e que, inscrito no Emmy Internacional, na categoria de novelas, esteja entre os cinco finalistas|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2017/11/rodrigo-santoro-participara-do-emmy-com-equipe-de-velho-chico.html|title=Rodrigo Santoro participar\u00e1 do Emmy com equipe do Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=14 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, convidado pela Globo, n\u00e3o poder\u00e1 ir: est\u00e1 filmando em S\u00e3o Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Lavoura Arcaica, 15 years on'' ===\nTribute was paid to the film ''[[To the Left of the Father]]'' in 2017, 15 years after it was made and on account of it being hailed as one of the most important Brazilian films of all time, at the [[Rio International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-renasce-15-anos-apos-sua-estreia-no-festival-do-rio/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' renasce, 15 anos ap\u00f3s sua estreia, no Festival do Rio|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=23 September 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um monumento cinematogr\u00e1fico de nossa Retomada}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/gente-boa/post/barulhinho-bom-exibicao-de-lavoura-arcaica-em-pelicula-faz-felicidade-dos-nostalgicos-no-festival-do-rio.html|title=Exibi\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica em pel\u00edcula faz a felicidade dos nost\u00e1lgicos no Festival do Rio |author=Cleo Guimaraes|date=15 October 2016|publisher=Gente Boa - OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Para Selton Mello, que interpreta o protagonista Andr\u00e9, \"Foi uma aventura emocional radical, que me tirou o ch\u00e3o e me fez renascer. Esse filme me deu coragem e a verdadeira dimens\u00e3o da minha profiss\u00e3o\u201d}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-e-homenageado-no-festival-do-rio,10000081767|title='Lavoura Arcaica' \u00e9 homenageado no Festival do Rio |author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=12 October 2016|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> and the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/lavoura-arcaica-com-presenca-de-radouan-nassar-poe-fim-a-mostra/|title='Lavoura Arcaica', com presen\u00e7a de Raduan Nassar, p\u00f5e fim \u00e0 Mostra|date=10 November 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|author=Luiz Zanin}}</ref> where a 35&nbsp;mm copy was shown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://revistacult.uol.com.br/home/lavoura-arcaica-e-a-utopia-por-um-mundo-melhor/|title=Lavoura Arcaica e a utopia por um mundo melhor|author=Eric Campi e Paulo Henrique Pompermaier|publisher=Revista Cult|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/lavoura-arcaica-15-anos-depois-dc69559029f7#.8409ildh4|title=Lavoura Arcaica, 15 anos depois|date=13 October 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-completa-15-anos-e-segue-arrebatador/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' completa 15 anos\u2026 e segue arrebatador|date=26 June 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|author=Rodrigo Fonseca}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/quinze-anos-apos-estreia-lavoura-arcaica-dialoga-com-discussoes-atuais-20291697|title=Quinze anos ap\u00f3s a estreia, Lavoura Arcaica dialoga com discuss\u00f5es atuais |author=Suzana Velasco|date=15 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> As part of the tribute at the [[Rio International Film Festival]], artist Raimundo Rodriguez created an installation that went on show for a month at the Esta\u00e7\u00e3o Net Botafogo, with memorabilia from the film, reviews and the director's notebooks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poltronapop.com.br/2016/10/festival-do-rio-2016-lavoura-arcaica.html|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha exibi\u00e7\u00e3o e instala\u00e7\u00e3o de Raimundo Rodriguez|date=23 September 2016|publisher=PoltronaPop|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> For Ismail Xavier and Ilana Feldman, Lavoura was born in 2001, emerging as a foreign body in the scenario of early 21st century Brazilian film, marked by its realism and its direct confrontation with Brazilian social and urban issues.<ref name=\"Ismail\"/>\n\n=== ''Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)'' ===\n{{Main|Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)}}\nScreened in 2017, the mini-series written by Maria Camargo based on the homonymous novel by [[Milton Hatoum]] was regarded by critics as another quality contribution to Brazilian television on account of the poetic style applied by the director to the adaptation of the novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|title=Duas adapta\u00e7\u00f5es para Dois Irm\u00e3os: Entrevista com Milton Hatoum|publisher=Literasutra|author=Monalisa Marques|date=13 March 2017|access-date=20 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421001906/https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|archive-date=21 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-faz-o-ano-comecar-muito-bem.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 um trabalho para ser louvado, uma grande contribui\u00e7\u00e3o de Carvalho para a televis\u00e3o brasileira|date=8 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://operamundi.uol.com.br/conteudo/samuel/46161/em+adaptacao+de+dois+irmaos+para+tv+luiz+fernando+carvalho+transforma+prosa+de+milton+hatoum+em+poesia.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho conseguiu transformar a prosa de Hatoum em poesia|author=Vera Ceccarello |date=12 January 2017|publisher=OperaMundi|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffpostbrasil.com/edianez-parente/a-teatralidade-que-faz-de-dois-irmaos-uma-obra-prima-da-televi_a_21698413/|title=A teatralidade que faz de 'Dois Irm\u00e3os' uma obra prima da televis\u00e3o|author=Edianez Parente|date=13 January 2017|publisher=The Huffington Post|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/dois-irmaos-e-a-versao-amazonica-de-caim-e-abel/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 a vers\u00e3o amaz\u00f4nica de Caim e Abel|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Pontuada por frases quase filos\u00f3ficas sobre a fala por vezes gaga do Tempo (outro muso de Carvalho), a vers\u00e3o de Maria Camargo para o romance de Hatoum deixa transbordante para o olhar quase teol\u00f3gico do aclamado diretor uma dimens\u00e3o b\u00edblica de fraternidade em f\u00faria, cindida na ponta da faca do ressentimento}}</ref> Direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso, costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie, scenography by Danielly Ramos, Juliana Carneiro and Mariana Villas-B\u00f4as, art production by Marco Cortez and Myriam Mendes. The production is part of the Quandrante Project and gained kudos with writer [[Milton Hatoum]]'s television debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://observador.pt/especiais/milton-hatoum-o-brasil-e-o-romance-da-desilusao/|title=Milton Hatoum: \"O Brasil \u00e9 o romance da desilus\u00e3o\"|author=Rita Cipriano |date=4 November 2017|publisher=Observador|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Milton Hatoum: \"O Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 um dos grandes diretores brasileiros. Dirigiu a adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica, do Raduan Nassar, e novelas importantes. A linguagem dele \u00e9 muito inovadora. N\u00e3o \u00e9 aquele pastel\u00e3o, aquele soap opera previs\u00edvel. Ele trabalha com uma linguagem muito criativa e pensa em tudo \u2014 nos figurinos, na luz, em cada detalhe. \u00c9 impressionante.\"}}</ref> According to the publishing house [[Companhia das Letras]], the book sales increased by some 500% after the start of the mini-series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gente.ig.com.br/tvenovela/2017-01-18/minisserie-dois-irmaos.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": miniss\u00e9rie aumenta vendas do livro em mais de 500%|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=iG}}</ref> Careers launched in Two Brothers include actors Matheus Abreu (Omar and Yaqub as an adolescent), the indigenous Zahy Guajajara (the \u00edndia Domingas) and the singer Bruna Caram (R\u00e2nia in the adult phase). The Lebanese actor [[Mounir Maasri]] made a guest appearance in the mini-series and was also responsible for the prosody (stress patterns) of the cast. The quality of the acting of the whole cast was stressed by the critics and also on social media and reached the worldwide and Brazilian Trending Topics throughout the series: [[Eliane Giardini]] and [[Juliana Paes]] as Zana; [[Antonio Fagundes]] and Antonio Calloni as Halim; and [[Cau\u00e3 Reymond]] and Matheus Abreu as the twins Omar and Yaqub. It was filmed in 2015, but at the request of the Globo network, the director agreed to make the novela ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' before he finished editing ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]'', which was shown in January 2017. A number of innovative relevant points in the director's language were highlighted: the relation between literature and the transposition into images,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/a-linguagem-como-sonho-17e89674f18#.ue4tuyxkc|title=A Linguagem como Sonho|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref> photography, framing, poetic language and sound track, which included hits from various decades to contextualize the period in which the mini-series was set. In addition, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated, on TV, the dialogue between the fictional scenes and images from the archives of Brazilian History, with the research of historical material done by Raquel Couto. \nAccording to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, in an article published in the Folha de S.Paulo newspaper about Netflix's investment in Brazil, the miniseries was a startling revelation to those who normally only have access to terrestrial channels in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2017/01/1852056-enquanto-netflix-avanca-na-conquista-do-mundo-globo-mostra-suas-armas.shtml|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 de uma qualidade espantosa para quem tem acesso apenas \u00e0 TV aberta no Brasil|date=21 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer}}</ref> For Luiz Zanin, the miniseries was about Brazil and the thwarted ideal of a multi-ethnic, sensual and carefree nation. \u201cAn elegant delicacy served up to the public, and which will leave it wanting more\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/o-som-e-a-furia-em-dois-irmaos/|title=O Som e a F\u00faria de Dois Irm\u00e3os|author=Luiz Zanin|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Uma hist\u00f3ria bem contada fala de si mesma e tamb\u00e9m de outras coisas. Esta nos falou do Brasil, de sua utopia frustrada de na\u00e7\u00e3o multi\u00e9tnica, sensual e feliz. Um fino biscoito oferecido ao p\u00fablico, e que vai deixar saudades}}</ref> Critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos wrote that what was seen in The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os) \u201cwas not a realistic reflection, but an exuberant image, a mythical saga, a work of art\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2017/01/09/arquetipos-e-epifanias-em-dois-irmaos/|title=Arqu\u00e9tipos e epifanias em Dois Irm\u00e3os|publisher=Rastros de Carmattos|author=Carlos Alberto Mattos|date=9 January 2017|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2017/01/09/dois-irmaos-transmite-em-belas-imagens-um-crescente-clima-de-tragedia/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' transmite em belas imagens um crescente clima de trag\u00e9dia|author=Nilson Xavier|date=9 January 2017|publisher=UOL|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=(A miniss\u00e9rie) tem a assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o que \u2013 j\u00e1 sabemos \u2013 significa esmero na est\u00e9tica, fotografia, tomadas, trilha sonora e dire\u00e7\u00e3o de atores.(...) Quem conhece a obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho sabe que cada produ\u00e7\u00e3o sua \u00e9 \u00fanica, mesmo dentro de seu estilo caracter\u00edstico de dire\u00e7\u00e3o}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://revistacaju.com.br/2017/01/13/a-lavoura-amazonense-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=A 'lavoura amazonense' de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Christiane Passafaro Guzzi|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Revista Caju|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=O que parece diferenciar Carvalho \u00e9 o estabelecimento de um estudo aprofundado da obra, da cr\u00edtica, da tradi\u00e7\u00e3o, e, principalmente, das reverbera\u00e7\u00f5es que a produ\u00e7\u00e3o dos escritores selecionados produzem no cen\u00e1rio ficcional}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/curioso-para-ver-dois-irmaos-ja-ha-3-episodios-no-globoplay-serie-vale-cada-minuto/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" em duas palavras: n\u00e3o perca|date=6 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|author=Cristina Padiglione}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/dois-irmaos-tem-adaptacao-sensivel-e-poetica-na-globo/|title=Carvalho volta a exibir seu estilo teatral, sens\u00edvel e po\u00e9tico na adapta\u00e7\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Veja|author=Meire Kusumoto}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/intensa-e-inquietante-dois-irmaos-fisga-o-publico-a-critica-e-prova-que-nao-e-preciso-ritmo-frenetico-para-fazer-sucesso|title=Intensa e inquietante, Dois Irm\u00e3os fisga o p\u00fablico, a cr\u00edtica e prova que n\u00e3o \u00e9 preciso ritmo fren\u00e9tico para fazer sucesso|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nexojornal.com.br/entrevista/2017/01/12/%E2%80%98Dois-irm%C3%A3os%E2%80%99-%C3%A9-sobre-o-colapso-de-uma-fam%C3%ADlia.-Mas-tamb%C3%A9m-de-um-projeto-de-pa%C3%ADs|title='Dois irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 sobre o colapso de uma fam\u00edlia. Mas tamb\u00e9m de um projeto de pa\u00eds|author=Juliana Domingos de Lima|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Nexo Jornal|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=\"A adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de \u201cDois irm\u00e3os\u201d, na verdade uma transposi\u00e7\u00e3o ou transcri\u00e7\u00e3o para o audiovisual, (...) oferece ao espectador brasileiro a possibilidade de alguns encontros fundamentais: encontro com cinquenta anos de hist\u00f3ria do pa\u00eds (...); com uma enorme diversidade humana e cultural (...); com uma forma expressiva que investe na sensibilidade e intelig\u00eancia do espectador (...); por fim, o encontro com um projeto de pa\u00eds, que se insinuava durante a Belle \u00c9poque amaz\u00f4nica, mas cuja promessa de futuro \u00e9 posta abaixo pela ditadura civil-militar e sua ideia destrutiva de \u201cprogresso\u201d. (...) \u00c9 importante perceber que, enquanto a literatura brasileira ganha relev\u00e2ncia e contund\u00eancia ao migrar para a TV, a pr\u00f3pria TV ganha tamb\u00e9m enorme prest\u00edgio art\u00edstico ao valorizar um produto liter\u00e1rio nacional, ainda mais sob a marca e o estilo barroco, marcado pelo ac\u00famulo de elementos e alta intensidade, do Luiz Fernando Carvalho\" (Ilana Feldman)}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Luiz Fernando Carvalho left the Globo Network (Rede Globo) after 30 years of working for the TV station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/desgastes-de-bastidores-motivaram-fim-do-contrato-do-diretor-de-dois-irmaos-na-globo/|title=Um diretor fora da curva|date=24 February 2017|publisher=Telepadi|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valor.com.br/cultura/4911882/um-diretor-fora-da-curva|title=Um diretor fora da curva|author=Maria da Paz Trefaut|date=24 March 2017|publisher=Valor Econ\u00f4mico|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho construiu uma aura intelectual ao seu redor, uma imagem de profissional autoral que n\u00e3o se apega a conven\u00e7\u00f5es}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the director received the APCA Award for ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/12/1942551-apca-escolhe-os-melhores-de-2017.shtml|title=APCA escolhe os melhores de 2017|date=11 December 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/juliana-paes-e-a-forca-do-querer-ganham-premio-da-associacao-paulista-de-criticos-de-artes-apca-veja-lista.ghtml|title=Juliana Paes e a For\u00e7a do Querer ganham pr\u00eamio da Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Artes (APCA); veja a lista|date=12 December 2017|publisher=G1|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref> the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] Nomination for ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and the Bravo Award (Pr\u00eamio Bravo) for Artist of the Year, for his trajectory and esthetic renovation on television with ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' and the 15th anniversary of the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''.\n\n=== ''The Passion According to G.H. (A Paix\u00e3o Segundo G.H.)'' ===\n{{Main|The Passion According to G.H. (film)}}\nFor the centennial of the birth of Clarice Lispector, in 2020, Carvalho is releasing a film adaptation of \"A Paix\u00e3o Segundo G.H.\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2018/11/apos-lavoura-arcaica-luiz-fernando-carvalho-adapta-obra-de-clarice.shtml|title=Ap\u00f3s Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho adapta obra de Clarice|author=Guilherme Genestreti|date=28 November 2018|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/luiz-fernando-carvalho-retoma-carreira-como-diretor-de-cinema-em-sp-22154367|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho retoma carreira como diretor de cinema em SP|author=Alessandro Giannini|date=6 December 2017| publisher=O Globo|access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref> The film is going to be released by the end of 2020, in celebration for the 100th anniversary of the birth of the author [[Clarice Lispector]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.folhadelondrina.com.br/colunistas/celia-musilli/iluminacoes-e-assombros-literarios-2979349e.html |title=Ilumina\u00e7\u00f5es e Assombros Liter\u00e1rios|author=Celia Musilli|date=11 January 2020|publisher=Folha de Londrina|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> Is the second feature film by the filmmaker after the award-winning [[To the Left of the Father]] (Portuguese: Lavoura Arcaica) (2001), also a cinematographic version of a classic of Brazilian literature. It was during the editing of \"Lavoura Arcaica\" that Luiz Fernando Carvalho had contact with G.H. - central novel of Clarice Lispector's work. The movie was entirely filmed in a penthouse of the neighbourhood of Copacabana, Rio de Janeiro, and presents [Maria Fernanda Candido] as the main character, G.H.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/maria-fernanda-candido-estara-em-versao-para-cinema-de-paixao-segundo-gh-22154286|title=Maria Fernanda C\u00e2ndido estar\u00e1 em vers\u00e3o para cinema de \"A Paix\u00e3o Segundo G.H.\"|author=Alessandro Giannini|date=6 December 2017| publisher=O Globo|access-date=29 January 2020|quote=\"Tenho uma afinidade grande com o Luiz. Esse aprofundamento que ele prop\u00f5e \u00e9 fundamental para realizarmos e desenvolvermos um trabalho. Gosto de como ele leva tudo isso e como prop\u00f5e o laborat\u00f3rio\".}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe was married to the artist Sandra Burgos, with whom he has one son, Th\u00e9o Burgos Carvalho.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Tereza Seiblitz]], with whom he has one son, Vitt\u00f3rio, born June 8, 2001.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]], with whom he has one son, Ariel.\n\n== Bibliography ==\nThe following books written by Luiz Fernando Carvalho are references for this article. For the complete list of books about the director, see [[Luiz Fernando Carvalho Bibliography]]\n* {{cite book |first = Luiz Fernando |last = Carvalho | title = Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme  | date = 2002  | publisher= Ateli\u00ea Editorial  | isbn = 9780815411833|url=https://books.google.com/?id=xNAed1GNO7QC&printsec=frontcover&dq=lavoura+arcaica#v=onepage&q=lavoura%20arcaica&f=false}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Abreu |first2=Luis Alberto |title=Hoje \u00e9 dia de Maria \u2013 Roteiros da 1a e 2a jornadas |publisher=Globo |date=2006 |isbn=9788525040985|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Qy8bAQAAIAAJ&q=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria&dq=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= Pedra do Reino - Estojo Ilustrado com 5 Cadernos de Filmagens + Di\u00e1rio de Elenco e Equipe |publisher=Globo |date=2007 |isbn=978-8525043375|url=http://www.saraiva.com.br/pedra-do-reino-estojo-ilustrado-com-5-cadernos-de-filmagens-diario-de-elenco-e-equipe-1968247.html}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= O processo de Capitu |publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra  |date=2008 |isbn=978-8577341023|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vaBaMQAACAAJ&dq=inauthor:%22Luiz+Fernando+Carvalho%22}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando|last=Carvalho |title= Livro - Quem \u00e9 Capitu?|publisher= Nova Fronteira |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=17\u201320| isbn=9788520920831|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DuUdAQAAIAAJ&q=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&dq=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj0-9O0ktTTAhWJl5AKHcKSBIIQ6AEIJjAA}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Diniz |first2=Julio|title= Machado de Assis (1908-2008) |publisher= Contraponto |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=80\u201383|isbn=978-85-7866-011-6|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Machado_de_Assis.html?id=cyyFPgAACAAJ&redir_esc=y}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Cuenca |first2=Jo\u00e3o Paulo |last3=Gianetti |first3=Cec\u00edlia |last4=Melamed |first4=Michel  |title= Afinal, o que querem as mulheres? |publisher= LeYa |date=2010 |isbn=9788580440300|url=https://books.google.com/?id=pwqCYgEACAAJ}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando |last2=Lins |first2=Paulo |last3=Franz |first3=Pedro |title=Suburbia |publisher=Aeroplano |date=2012 |isbn=9788578200916 |url=http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |access-date=2017-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112022818/http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |archive-date=2017-11-12 |url-status=dead }}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho |title= Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra |date=2013 |isbn=978-85-7734-525-0|url=https://books.google.com/?id=sHngjgEACAAJ}}\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Cinema\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' \n| Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Short-film]] based on [[Roland Barthes]]\u00b4s Fragments d'un discours amoureux\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Ohos Sejam Atendidos)]]''\n| Director\n| [[Documentary film]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''\n|  Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Film]] based on the novel of [[Raduan Nassar]]\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The_Passion_According_to_G.H._(film)|The Passion According to G.H.]]''\n|  Director and Screenwriter\n|  [[Film]] based on the novel of [[Clarice Lispector]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+TV Series\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas (miniss\u00e9rie)|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'' \n| Assistant director\n| Based on [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]]\u00b4s [[Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)|Sweet River (Riacho Doce)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]''\n|  Director \n| Based on [[E\u00e7a de Queiroz]]\u00b4s [[Os Maias]]\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[:pt:Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada|Today is Maria's Day: Second Journey (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel; Co-written with Braulio Tavares and Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Capitu]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Machado de Assis]]\u00b4s [[Dom Casmurro]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?|After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Influenced by [[Sigmund Freud]]\u00b4s theory; Co-written with J.P. Cuenca and Michel Melamed\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[:pt:Sub\u00farbia|Suburbia]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Co-written with Paulo Lins\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' \n| Novelist e Diretor\n|  From [[Clarice Lispector]]\u00b4s chronicles\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Milton Hatoum]]\u00b4s novel\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Soap Opera\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Helena (1987)|Helena]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Machado de Assis]]\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Carmem (telenovela)|Carmen]]''\n|  Director\n| Written by [[Gl\u00f3ria Perez]]\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[:pt:Vida Nova|Vida Nova]]''\n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Tieta (telenovela)|Tieta]]''\n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Jorge Amado]]\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Pedra sobre Pedra|Stone on Stone (Pedra sobre Pedra)]]''\n| Director\n| Written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]]\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Renascer|Rebirth (Renascer)]]''\n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:Irm\u00e3os Coragem (1995)|Irm\u00e3os Coragem]]''\n| Director\n| Remake of [[Janete Clair]]\u00b4s soap opera\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of Catlle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Esperan\u00e7a (telenovela)|Esperan\u00e7a]]'' \n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Bruno Luperi\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Especiais para TV\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Chit\u00e3ozinho e Xoror\u00f3 Especial'' \n| Director\n| Musical Show\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' \n| Director\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol|A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexandre and Others Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'' \n|  Diretor\n| Based on [[Graciliano Ramos]]\u00b4s short stories\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://luizfernandocarvalho.com/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Official website] {{in lang|pt}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0142461|name=Luiz Fernando Carvalho}}* \n* [http://40.mostra.org/en/filme/3902-TO-THE-LEFT-OF-THE-FATHER To The Left of The Father - Mostra de Cinema de SP]\n* [http://www.commeaucinema.com/critiques/a-la-gauche-du-pere,14209 A La Gauche du Pere - Comme au Cinema] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html A La Gauche du Pere - AlloCine] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://enciclopedia.itaucultural.org.br/pessoa466999/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Enciclopedia Ita\u00fa Cultural] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://topicos.estadao.com.br/noticias-sobre-luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Estad\u00e3o] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Ateli\u00ea Editorial] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://40.mostra.org/br/diretores/3359-LUIZ-FERNANDO-CARVALHO Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Mostra de Cinema de SP] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.filmeb.com.br/quem-e-quem/diretor/luiz-fernando-carvalho Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Filme B] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.adorocinema.com/personalidades/personalidade-78430/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Adoro Cinema] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [http://www.festivaldorio.com.br/br/filmes/lavoura-arcaica Lavoura Arcaica - Festival do Rio] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://twitter.com/luizfernandodir Luiz Fernando Carvalho] no [[Twitter]] {{in lang|pt}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/LuizFernandoCarvalhoFanPage Luiz Fernando Carvalho] no [[Facebook]] {{in lang|pt}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Carvalho, Luiz Fernando}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Brazilian film directors]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox person\n| name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho\n| image    =\n| imagesize =\n| birth_name = Luiz Fernando Carvalho de Almeida\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1960|7|28|mf=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality =\n| alias =\n| yearsactive = 1985\u2013present\n| occupation       = Film director, screenwriter, novelist\n| known_for        = [[Film]]s and [[Television program|TV series]] based on [[List of Brazilian writers|Brazilian writers]]\n| notable_works   =  ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|Os Maias]]'', ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]''\n| children = \n}}\n\n'''Luiz Fernando Carvalho''' (born July 28, 1960 in [[Rio de Janeiro]]) is a [[Brazil]]ian filmmaker and television director, known for works closely linked to literature that constitute a renovation in Brazilian audiovisual aesthetics.<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://escholarship.org/uc/item/589368qf#page-3 \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho: An Auteur of Brazilian Television\"], ''UCLA Electronic Theses and Dissertations'', 2013. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref> He has already brought to the screen works by [[Ariano Suassuna]], [[Raduan Nassar]], [[Machado de Assis]], [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]], [[Roland Barthes]], [[Clarice Lispector]], [[Milton Hatoum]], [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and [[Graciliano Ramos]], among others.\n\nSome critics compare Luiz Fernando Carvalho's productions to the Brazilian Cinema Novo<ref name=\"Sukman\">{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=lavoura+arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=Mario+Peixoto&decadaSelecionada=&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Um cineasta que est\u00e1 entrando para o clube dos poetas|author=Hugo Sukman|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho respeita uma tradi\u00e7\u00e3o que vai de Mario Peixoto a Ruy Guerra}}</ref> and icons of film history such as [[Luchino Visconti]] and [[Andrei Tarkovski]].<ref name=\"Piza\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-estreia-sabado-no-canada,20010822p2443|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" estr\u00e9ia s\u00e1bado no Canad\u00e1|author=Daniel Piza|date=22 August 2001|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um parentesco com o estilo e a espiritualidade do cinema dos russos Tarkovski e Sokurov}}</ref> His work is characterized by visual and linguistic experimentation<ref name=\"Ismail\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrissima/2016/10/1822788-quinze-anos-depois-filme-lavoura-arcaica-ainda-e-corpo-estranho.shtml|title=Quinze anos depois, filme \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ainda \u00e9 corpo estranho|author=Ilana Feldman e Ismail Xavier|date=16 October 2016|publisher=Ilustr\u00edssima/Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and exploration of the multiplicity of Brazil's cultural identity.<ref>[http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil\"], ''La N\u00e1cion'', 11 May 2002. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref name=\"MariaRita\">{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/maria-rita-kehl-velho-chico-reinaugura-um-desejo-de-utopia-20210647|title='Velho Chico' reinaugura um desejo de utopia|author=Maria Rita Kehl|date=1 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=O Brasil de Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 agreste. \u00c9 pobre, remediado, devastado e esperan\u00e7oso}}</ref> The baroque style<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diplomatique.org.br/uma-novela-shakespeareana-neorrealista-e-barroca/|title='Uma Novela Shakespearana, neorrealista e barroca|author=Helcio Kovaleski|date=15 March 2016|publisher=Le Monde Diplomatique Brasil|access-date=13 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Coelho\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1411200117.htm|title='Lavoura' e os ind\u00edcios de uma obra prima|author=Marcelo Coelho|date=14 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Lavoura Arcaica\" tem todas as raz\u00f5es para ser excessivo, barroco, quase ostentat\u00f3rio em sua riqueza estil\u00edstica. O filme consegue traduzir visualmente toda a beleza liter\u00e1ria do livro de Raduan Nassar}}</ref><ref name=\"Ilana\">{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/dois-irm%C3%A3os-arqueologia-da-mem%C3%B3ria-alegoria-da-destrui%C3%A7%C3%A3o-45b5723b88cd|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os: arqueologia da mem\u00f3ria, alegoria da destrui\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ilana Feldman|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Na obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o barroco \u00e9 um conceito norteador de uma pesquisa de linguagem: busca conceitual pela brasilidade presente nos opostos, nas contradi\u00e7\u00f5es e nos contrastes deste pa\u00eds}}</ref> of overlays and interlacing of narrative genres, the relation to the moment in Time,<ref name=\"Mata\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/critica/ult569u395.shtml|title=Em \"Lavoura Arcaica\", Carvalho faz retrato do tempo|author=Tiago Mata Machado|date=23 October 2001|publisher=FolhaOnline|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> the archetypal symbols of the Earth and the reflection on the language of social and family melodrama<ref name=\"Inacio\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1511200125.htm|title=Longa \u00e9 exce\u00e7\u00e3o exemplar no cinema do pa\u00eds|author=In\u00e1cio Ara\u00fajo|date=15 November 2001|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> are features of the director's poetic language.\n\nThe filmmaker's works have met with both critical and public acclaim. He directed the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'' (2001)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://journals.openedition.org/cinelatino/2104|title=Du go\u00fbt du public selon Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Sylvie Debs|date=1 June 2008|publisher=Cin\u00e9mas d\u2019Am\u00e9rique latine|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/archives/article/2003/07/09/a-la-gauche-du-pere-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho_327204_1819218.html|title=\"A la gauche du p\u00e8re\", de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Florence Colombani|date=9 July 2003|publisher=Le Monde|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>, based on the homonymous novel by [[Raduan Nassar]], cited by the critic [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]] as a \"ground-breaking promise of renovation, of an upheaval not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]],<ref name=\"Cahiers\">Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.cineressources.net/articles_periodiques/resultat_f/index.php?pk=85803&param=F&textfield=a+la+gauche+du+pere&rech_type=F&rech_mode=exact&pageF=1&pageP=1&type=FOR&pk_recherche=85803 \" Les pieds dans la terre\"], ''Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma'', July\u2013August 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref><ref>Tess\u00e9, Jean-Philippe [http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/ \"On peut ais\u00e9ment voir dans cette grande fresque charnelle la plus belle d\u00e9couverte du cin\u00e9ma br\u00e9silien depuis Glauber Rocha, au moins parce que Luiz Fernando Carvalho partage avec le r\u00e9alisateur de Antonio das mortes un go\u00fbt pour la puissance du lyrisme\"], ''Chronicart'', 6 July 2003. Retrieved on 19 April 2017.</ref> which won over 50 national and international awards.<ref name=\"Montreal\">{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,montreal-premia-a-ousadia-de-lavoura-arcaica,20010905p2499 |title=Montreal premia a ousadia de \"Lavoura Arcaica\"|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=5 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The telenovelas ''[[Renascer|Renascer (Rebirth)]]'' (1993) and ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' (1996), by screenwriter [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, are recognized as benchmarks of Brazilian television drama and achieved some of the highest audience ratings of the 1990s.<ref>Hopewell, John [https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/rodrigo-santoro-globo-velho-chico-1201725234/ \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho (\u2018The King of the Cattle\u2019) returns with a rural romantic saga packing political overtones\"], ''Variety'', 8 March 2016. Retrieved on 05 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tv-pesquisa.com.puc-rio.br/mostraregistro.asp?CodRegistro=23342&PageNo=25|title=Renascer deu aula de dire\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|date=6 November 1993|publisher=Jornal do Brasil|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\nThere is a marked contrast between the director's television works: from the pop design of the 60s in the series ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' (2013) to the classic rigor of the mini-series ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]'' (2001), the urban references of the working-class suburbs in the mini-series ''[[:pt:Suburbia|Suburbia]]'' (2012) to the playfulness of the soap ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' (2014), the aesthetic research of the Sert\u00e3o (backcountry) in ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' (2016) to the Brazilian fairytale of the mini-series ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005) and the realistic universe of family tragedy in ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' (2017).<ref>Carter, Eli Lee [http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt \"Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu\"], ''University of Virginia'', 2014. Retrieved on 18 April 2017.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660| title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction| journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies| volume=23| issue=4| pages=363\u2013379| year=2014| last1=Carter| first1=Eli Lee}}</ref>\n\nThe director's production process is renowned for identifying new talent from all over Brazil and for training actors,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/geral,freud-explica,635078|title=Freu Explica|author=Patricia Vilalba|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=11 November 2010|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Freud explica: \"O processo de ensaios para filmar com Luiz Fernando \u00e9 um dos diferenciais do diretor, que o p\u00f4s em posi\u00e7\u00e3o de sonho de consumo de qualquer ator comprometido com seu of\u00edcio\"}}</ref> revealing new stars of the dramatic arts such as [[Leticia Sabatella]], [[Eliane Giardini]], [[Bruna Linzmeyer]], Johnny Massaro, [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Marcello Antony]], Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]], [[Giselle Iti\u00e9]], Emilio Orciollo Netto, Sheron Menezes, Jackson Antunes, [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], [[Eduardo Moscovis]], Jackson Costa, [[Leonardo Vieira]], Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Luciana Braga, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es, Cyria Coentro, Marina Nery, J\u00falio Machado, B\u00e1rbara Reis, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro and Lucy Alves, among others. The director's actor coaching technique has given rise to a method recounted in the book ''O processo de cria\u00e7\u00e3o dos atores de Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (''The creation process of the actors in Dois Irm\u00e3os''), by the photographer Leandro Pagliaro.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/tv/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-livro-registra-cenas-da-preparacao-do-elenco-da-minisserie-9303834.html/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": livro registra cenas da prepara\u00e7\u00e3o do elenco da miniss\u00e9rie|author=Roger Lerina|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/literatura,fotografo-registra-o-intenso-processo-de-ensaio-da-serie-dois-irmaos,10000098867|title=Fot\u00f3grafo registra o intenso processo de ensaio da s\u00e9rie 'Dois Irm\u00e3os'|author=Ubiratan Brasil|date=9 January 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote box|width=40%|align=right|quote=\"There is a concrete promise of renovation, of a palpitation not seen in Brazilian cinema since [[Glauber Rocha]]. (...) At first, one is left with nothing but fragments torn from a visual magma. But soon the chaos resolves itself, the film unrolls in all its richness like a barbaric poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power. (...) Never, however, does its return to the underlying myths obscure or accelerate the predominance of the sensations. If the film is possessed of such enchanting force, it is because Luiz Fernando Carvalho knows that everything starts there, in this first way of being born into the world, of allowing oneself to be ravished by it, to savor every twist of it...\"|source=\u2014Les Cahiers du Cin\u00e8ma, by [[:fr:Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9]] on his critic about ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''<ref name=\"Cahiers\"/>}}\n\n== Early Career: 1980s ==\nLuiz Fernando Carvalho studied architecture and literature. He started out in cinema at 18 in a number of roles: audio technician, assistant director, screenwriter, short film editor and director. His first TV work came in the early 80s, as assistant director of noteworthy mini-series, such as ''[[O Tempo e o Vento]]'', based on the work of [[\u00c9rico Ver\u00edssimo]], directed by [[Paulo Jos\u00e9]], and ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'', from the work of [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa|Jo\u00e3o Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]], in which he started to direct his first scenes, still as assistant director to Walter Avancini.\n\n=== ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' ===\nHe wrote and directed the short ''The Waiting (A Espera)'', based on the book ''[[A Lover's Discourse: Fragments]]'' (''Fragments d'un discours amoureux'') by [[Roland Barthes]]. Launched in 1986, the film collected the following awards: Best Short Film, Best Actress ([[Marieta Severo]]) and Best Cinematography ([[Walter Carvalho]]) at the 13th [[Festival de Gramado]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|title=Lista de vencedores do Festival de Gramado de 1986|publisher=FestivaldeGramado.net|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104050/http://www.festivaldegramado.net/vencedores?vencedores=30|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Best Short Film ([[Golden Shell]]) at the [[San Sebasti\u00e1n International Film Festival]] (Spain); and the Special Jury Award at the Ste Ther\u00e8se Festival (Canada).\n\n== 1990s ==\n=== ''Sweet River (Riacho Doce)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nEarly in the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed a 40-chapter mini-series written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], based on the work of [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]] and starring [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]], Osmar Prado, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, [[Carlos Alberto Riccelli]] and [[Fernanda Montenegro]], with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The then inhospitable island of Fernando de Noronha (PE) served as the scene for the story, which is set in a small fishing village in the Northeast of Brazil.\n\n=== ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' ===\nIn 1991, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed an adaptation of a script by Brazilian TV pioneer P\u00e9ricles Leal, with costumes by Beth Filipecki. The telefilm was shot in the town of Canind\u00e9, Cear\u00e1, and reached the finals of the 34th [[New York Television Festival]]. This marked the television debut of actress [[Leticia Sabatella]]. The critic Rodrigo Fonseca affirmed that his first memory of Let\u00edcia Sabatella on TV was also when he discovered the existence of the \"genius of direction that is Luiz Fernando\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mulheresdocinemabrasileiro.com.br/site/entrevistas_depoimentos/visualiza/164/Rodrigo-Fonseca-Leticia-Sabatella|title=Let\u00edcia Sabatella, por Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=Mulheres do Cinema Brasileiro|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Foi quando eu tomei contato com a exist\u00eancia desse g\u00eanio da dire\u00e7\u00e3o que \u00e9 o Luiz Fernando}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Stone on Stone (Pedra Sobre Pedra)'' ===\n{{Main|Pedra Sobre Pedra}}\nIn 1992, he directed the telenovela written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]], considered to have reached the 6th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\">{{cite web|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0,,EMI63532-9531,00.html |title=Aguinaldo Silva divulga lista das novelas com maior audi\u00eancia da hist\u00f3ria |date=10 March 2009 |publisher=Revista Quem |access-date=14 April 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045233/http://revistaquem.globo.com/Revista/Quem/0%2C%2CEMI63532-9531%2C00.html |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>  Notable cast members included: [[Lima Duarte]], [[Renata Sorrah]], Armando B\u00f3gus, [[Eva Wilma]], [[Paulo Betti]], [[Andr\u00e9a Beltr\u00e3o]], Pedro Paulo Rangel and [[Eduardo Moscovis]]. Certain characters are regarded as landmarks in TV drama: Sergio Cabeleira (Osmar Prado) and the photographer Jorge Tadeu ([[F\u00e1bio Jr.]]).\n\n=== ''The Tale of Our Lady of Light (O Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz)'' ===\nWhile filming [[Pedra sobre Pedra]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho came up with a significant sequence inspired by [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s  Armorial Movement (Movimento Armorial) . The enormous success of the sequence, confirmed by the record number of requests by viewers for a rerun, was decisive in transformation of the material into a telefilm, with additional scenes written by Braulio Tavares and interpreted by the actor and musician [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]]. It competed for the [[International Emmy Award]] in 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|title=Curiosidades do Auto de Nossa Senhora da Luz|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415104038/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/especiais/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz/auto-de-nossa-senhora-da-luz-curiosidades.htm|archive-date=15 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Rebirth (Renascer)'' ===\n{{Main|Renascer}}\nThe 1993 soap, written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, met with critical and public acclaim and was the most watched in the 90s and 4th in audience ratings in the history of Brazilian television.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was also shown in several other countries. As directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, it is regarded as among the symbols of renovation of the aesthetics of the genre in the 90s.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KkJNHsGCYFkC&pg=PA219&lpg=PA219 |last=Jacob de Souza |first=Maria Carmen |title=Telenovela e representa\u00e7\u00e3o social: Benedito Ruy Barbosa e a representa\u00e7\u00e3o do popular na novela Renascer|publisher=E-papers|year=2004 |page=219 |isbn=978-85-87922-90-8|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, um dos mais expressivos representantes contempor\u00e2neos dessa tend\u00eancia autoral da dire\u00e7\u00e3o de telenovela, fez de Renascer seu sucesso mais exemplar}}</ref> The character Buba, interpreted by [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]], caused a national controversy, as it was the first time that the discussion of gender had been addressed in a telenovela. It received the APCA Award for Best Novela, Best Actor ([[Antonio Fagundes]]), Best Supporting Actor (Osmar Prado), Best Supporting Actress (Regina Dourado), Best Male Breakthrough Performance (Jackson Antunes).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/6/02/ilustrada/21.html/|title=\"Renascer\" domina premia\u00e7\u00e3o de cr\u00edticos|author=Ana Beatriz Brisola|date=2 June 1994|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> [[Leonardo Vieira]], Jackson Antunes, Cac\u00e1 Carvalho, Marco Ricca, [[Isabel Fillardis]] and [[Maria Luisa Mendon\u00e7a]] were among the talents revealed in this work. The television entrepreneur [[:pt:Boni|Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira]], considered the plot \"well structured by Benedito, with a well-crafted first part, masterfully directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Oliveira |first=Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio |date=2011 |title=O Livro do Boni |language=pt |location=S\u00e3o Paulo |publisher=Casa da Palavra |isbn=978-85-7734-226-6}}</ref> According to Marilia Martins, few novelas had a first chapter directed with such polish and skill as ''Rebirth''.\n\n=== ''A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol}}\nIn 1994, the telefilm directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho marked the first appearance of [[Ariano Suassuna]]'s works on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/3/09/ilustrada/2.html|title=Ariano Suassuna prepara estr\u00e9ia na TV|author=Marcelo Migliaccio|date=9 March 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=10 April 2017}}</ref> Based on the writer's unpublished novel of the same name, the script was the work of Ariano himself, in partnership with the director. Director of photography Dib Lufti, costumes by Luciana Buarque and art production by Lia Renha. Scenography by the artist Fernando Velloso, from the [[Grupo Corpo]] dance group, music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira, a member of the Armorial Quintet (Quinteto Armorial). With ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', the director commenced his exploration of the limits of television language, combining elements of the popular theater of the Northeast. Luiz Carlos Vasconcelos's Grupo Piolim participated and the cast included Tereza Seiblitz, Lineu Dias, Sebasti\u00e3o Vasconcelos, Ana L\u00facia Torre, [[Raul Cortez]] and the then novice actor Floriano Peixoto. According to the researcher of Literature H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es, the work gave rise to an impasse at the TV station: was Lu\u00edz Fernando Carvalho too big for the Globo screen?<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1994/7/14/ilustrada/9.html|title=\"Mulher Vestida de Sol\" desafia o padr\u00e3o de realismo da Globo|author=H\u00e9lio Guimar\u00e3es|date=14 July 1994|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)}}\nOne year after ''A Woman dressed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)'', in 1995, Luiz Fernando Carvalho resumed his connection with the writer [[Ariano Suassuna]], this time transforming the play ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]'' into a telefilm . The director continued his search for a hybrid language for television, as a way of criticizing the naturalism of the novelas. Art production and costumes by Yurika Yamasaki and the artist Dantas Suassuna, participation of [[Antonio N\u00f3brega]], [[Patr\u00edcia Fran\u00e7a]], [[Ary Fontoura]] and [[Marieta Severo]]. According to the critic Rog\u00e9rio Durst, the telefilm was a major feat of TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=artigo&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=A+Farsa+da+Boa+Pregui%C3%A7a&anyword=&noword=&exactword=sofisticada&decadaSelecionada=1990&anoSelecionado=&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title= Uma sofisticada op\u00e7\u00e3o popular|author=Rog\u00e9rio Durst|publisher=O Globo|date= 7 December 1995|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)'' ===\n{{Main Article|O Rei do Gado}}\n''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', 1996, the director's next collaboration with the author [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/novela-de-forte-cunho-social-rei-do-gado-de-benedito-ruy-barbosa-volta-ao-ar-nesta-segunda-15009118|title= Novela de forte cunho social, 'O rei do gado', de Benedito Ruy Barbosa, volta ao ar nesta segunda|author=Nat\u00e1lia Borde |publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=12 January 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> became the novela with the 9th largest audience in Brazilian television history.<ref name=\"Audiencia\"/> It was rescreened three times,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/19/diretor-explica-por-que-terceira-reprise-de-rei-do-gado-faz-tanto-sucesso/|title=Diretor explica por que terceira reprise de \"Rei do Gado\" faz tanto sucesso|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=19 February 2015|publisher=UOL|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2015/02/1582950-reprise-de-o-rei-do-gado-chega-a-bater-novelas-ineditas-em-audiencia.shtml|title=Reprise de 'O Rei do Gado' chega a bater novelas in\u00e9ditas em audi\u00eancia|author=Fernanda Reis|date=1 February 2015|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> outrating other productions of the time, and was sold to over 30 countries. It marked the debut of [[Marcello Antony]], [[Caco Ciocler]], [[Mariana Lima]], Emilio Orciollo Netto and [[Lav\u00ednia Vlasak]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1996/10/20/revista_da_folha/3.html|title= Vidas com rumo|publisher=Revista da Folha|date=20 October 1996|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  Other significant aspects of the novela were its social criticism and sensitive approach to the Landless Workers Movement (movimento dos sem-terra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/direto-da-fonte/a-televisao-brasileira-tem-dado-claros-sinais-de-esgotamento-de-seu-modelo/|title=A televis\u00e3o brasileira tem dado claros sinais de esgotamento de seu modelo|author=Thais Arbex|date=16 December 2013|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote= Rei do Gado foi a primeira novela a abordar o conflito dos sem-terra e a reforma agr\u00e1ria}}</ref> The actors Jackson Antunes and [[Ana Beatriz Nogueira]] stand out in this context. The cast included [[Antonio Fagundes]], [[Patricia Pillar]], [[Leticia Spiller]] and [[Raul Cortez]] with guest appearances in the early stages by [[Tarcisio Meira]], [[Eva Wilma]] and [[Vera Fischer (actress)|Vera Fischer]]. The character Ti\u00e3o Galinha, interpreted by Osmar Prado, is a landmark of his career. The novela received the Certificate of Merit at the [[San Francisco International Film Festival]] and the APCA Award for Best Actor ([[Raul Cortez]]), Best Supporting Actor (Leonardo Br\u00edcio), Best Supporting Actress (Walderez de Barros) and Best Male Breakthrough Performance ([[Caco Ciocler]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|title=Pr\u00eamios de'O Rei do Gado'|publisher=Mem\u00f3ria Globo|access-date=14 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170328091627/http://memoriaglobo.globo.com/programas/entretenimento/novelas/o-rei-do-gado/premios.htm|archive-date=28 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Fernando de Barros e Silva wrote, in the Folha de S.Paulo, \"The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado) swallows up Brazilian cinema\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=O+Rei+do+Gado+engole+o+cinema+nacional+&site=&periodo=acervo&x=14&y=13|title=O Rei do Gado engole o cinema nacional |author=Fernando de Barros e Silva|date=7 July 1996|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to critic Rogerio Durst, the novela is \"a dramatic epic with first class special appearances and superb photography\".\n\nTiao Galinha belongs to another soap opera: \u201cRenascer\u201d.\n\n=== ''Giovanna and Henrico (Giovanna e Henrico)'' ===\nThe quality of the first seven chapters of ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of the Cattle (O Rei do Gado)]]'', showing the decline of the coffee cycle and Brazil's participation in World War II, prompted The Globo Network's International Division to transform the first part of the novela into the mini-series ''Giovanna and Henrico'', with [[Let\u00edcia Spiller]] and Leonardo Br\u00edcio playing the lead couple. The production was selected as hors-concours at the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq150522.htm|title='O Rei do Gado' ganha pr\u00eamios em festivais|author=Cristina Padiglione|date=15 May 1997|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos}}\nBefore the end of the 90s, Luiz Fernando Carvalho had already started on research for the feature film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''. Together with the author of the novel, [[Raduan Nassar]], he traveled to the Lebanon to familiarize himself with Mediterranean culture. The material collected during the trip was used to produce the documentary ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos)]]'', screened on GNT in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/1997/12/14/tv_folha/16.html |title='Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos' estr\u00e9ia no GNT|author=Mariana Scalzo|date=14 December 1997 |access-date=29 March 2017}}</ref> In the opinion of critic Rodrigo Fonseca, the documentary \"honed to the limit of tragic fatality its investigation of time\".\n\n== 2000s ==\n=== ''To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' ===\n{{Main Article|To the Left of the Father}}\nIn 2001, the director made his first feature film, ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]'', in which he was responsible for directing, screenplay and editing, with cinematography by Walter Carvalho, art direction by Yurika Yamazaki and costume design by Beth Filipecki.<ref name=\"Sukman\"/><ref name=\"Piza\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|title=Com Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho vence o desafio de levar a literatura de Raduan Nassar para o cinema|author=Almir de Freitas|publisher=Revista Bravo!|access-date=17 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170418082444/http://www.almirdefreitas.com.br/almir/Lavoura_Arcaica___Luiz_Fernando_Carvalho.html|archive-date=18 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The cast included [[Selton Mello]], [[Raul Cortez]], [[Simone Spoladore]], [[Leonardo Medeiros]], [[Caio Blat]] and [[Juliana Carneiro da Cunha]]. Aiming to maintain the connection with the poetic prose of [[Raduan Nassar]]'s book, the director elected to film without a defined script, based entirely on the actors' improvisations on the theme.<ref name=\"Mata\"/><ref name=\"Coelho\"/><ref name=\"Inacio\"/> This involved intensive coaching of the cast, secluded on a farm for four months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1408200518.htm|title=Mergulho em Raduan Nassar conduz a pequena obra-prima|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|date=14 August 2005|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The film's creation and production process was discussed in the book ''About To the Left of The Father'' (\"Sobre Lavoura Arcaica\"), in which the director is interviewed by Jos\u00e9 Carlos Avellar, Geraldo Sarno, Miguel Pereira, Ivana Bentes, Arnaldo Carrilho and Liliane Heynemann, launched in Portuguese, English and French by the publisher [[:pt:Ateli\u00ea Editorial|Ateli\u00ea Editorial]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://www.atelie.com.br/publicacoes/autor/luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title= Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho |publisher=Atelier Cultural |year=2002|isbn=978-85-7480-140-7|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It was success with the critics<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&pagina=&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=Lavoura+Arcaica&anyword=&noword=&exactword=colheita&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2001&mesSelecionado=&diaSelecionado=|title=Uma colheita espl\u00eandida|author=Luciano Trigo|publisher=RioShow|date=28 October 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.folha.uol.com.br/resultados/?q=Filme+radicaliza+linguagem&site=&periodo=acervo&x=22&y=15|title=Filme radicaliza linguagem|author=Jos\u00e9 Geraldo Couto|publisher=Ilustrada/Folha de S.Paulo|date=24 September 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.estadao.com.br/pagina/#!/20011125-39485-spo-151-cd2-d3-not/busca/Lavoura+Arcaica|title=Convuls\u00f5es|author=Daniel Piza|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/395562-luiz-fernando-carvalho-talento-made-in-brasil|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, talento made in Brasil|author=Diego Batle|publisher=La Nacion|language=spanish|date=11 May 2002|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> and the public, reaching 300 thousand viewers with just two copies, one in Rio de Janeiro and the other in S\u00e3o Paulo. It is considered one of the [[Abraccine Top 100 Brazilian films|100 best Brazilian films of all times]], according to the Brazilian Film Critics Association (Abraccine).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://abraccine.org/2015/11/27/abraccine-organiza-ranking-dos-100-melhores-filmes-brasileiros/ |title= Abraccine organiza ranking dos 100 melhores filmes brasileiros |access-date= 26 October 2016 |author= Andr\u00e9 Dib |date= 27 November 2015 |publisher= abraccine.org}}</ref> It had a successful career in a number of national and international festivals, receiving over 50 awards at the [[Montreal World Film Festival]],<ref name=\"Montreal\"/><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.ffm-montreal.org/en/awards/16-awards-of-the-montreal-world-film-festival-2001.html/|title = 16 Awards of the Montreal World Film Festival 2001|website=FFMMontreal.org|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=n.d.|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Rio Film Festival]], the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]], the [[Grande Pr\u00eamio do Cinema Brasileiro|Grand Prix for Brazilian Film]], the [[Bras\u00edlia Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq2911200111.htm|title = Bras\u00edlia celebra \"Lavoura\" e \"Samba\"|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=29 November 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Havana Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1512200135.htm|title = \"Lavoura\" ganha pr\u00eamios em Havana|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=15 December 2001|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Cartagena Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1103200214.htm|title = \"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha Festival de Cartagena|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=<!--Not stated-->|date=11 March 2002|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> the [[Guadalajara International Film Festival]], the [[Buenos Aires International Festival of Independent Cinema]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pagina12.com.ar/diario/espectaculos/6-4799-2002-05-06.html|title=Una met\u00e1fora sobre los que no tienen lugar en la mesa social|author=Ana Bianco|language=spanish|publisher=P\u00e1gina 12|date=1 May 2002|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> among others. In the opinion of writer and psychoanalyst Renato Tardivo, author of ''Porvir que vem antes de tudo \u2013 literatura e cinema em Lavoura Arcaica'', the film is one of the most important works of Brazilian cinema \u201cof all times\u201d.<ref>{{cite book |last=Tardivo |first=Renato Cury  |title=Porvir que vem antes de tudo: uma leitura de lavoura arcaica - literatura, cinema e a unidade dos sentidos |publisher=Universidade de S\u00e3o Paulo (USP)|date=2009 |url= http://www.teses.usp.br/teses/disponiveis/47/47134/tde-11122009-110032/pt-br.php}}</ref> The critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos described it as the first work of art of the Brazilian cinema in the 21st century.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2016/10/13/festival-do-rio-lavoura-arcaica/|title=Festival do Rio: Lavoura Arcaica|author=Carlos Alberto de Mattos|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|date=25 November 2001|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The film was acclaimed by the critics of various countries and, according to the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], ''To the Left of the Father'' is a \"barbarous poem verging on hallucination, of extraordinary power\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.chronicart.com/cinema/a-la-gauche-du-pere/|title=Critique:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|author=Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9|language=French|publisher=Chronicart|date=6 July 2003|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\">{{cite web| url=http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html|title=Critiques:A La Gauche du P\u00e8re|publisher=AlloCin\u00e9|language=French|access-date=19 April 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"allocine.fr\"/><ref>{{cite web| url=http://next.liberation.fr/cinema/2003/07/09/pere-de-tous-les-vices_439245|title=P\u00e9re de touts les vices. Relecture saisissante d'un monstre de la litt\u00e9rature br\u00e9silienne|author=Didier Peron|language=French|date=9 July 2003|publisher=Liber\u00e1cion|access-date=22 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''The Maias (Os Maias)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)}}\nA 2001 production, this mini-series based on the homonymous novel by [[E\u00e7a de Queir\u00f3s]] and adapted by Maria Adelaide Amaral was another landmark in the director's career.<ref>Elena Corr\u00eaa, \"Linguagem po\u00e9tica que remete a outra \u00e9poca. Roteiro fiel e dire\u00e7\u00e3o inconfund\u00edvel\", em \"O Globo\" (11 de janeiro de 2001)</ref> The Maias portrays the decadent Portuguese aristocracy in the second half of the 19th century, through the tragic story of a traditional Lisbon family. Costumes by Beth Filipecki and direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro. In the opinion of writer [[Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo]], \"the extraordinarily mobile camera of Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u201cvisited\u201d, more than portrayed, the frivolous Lisbon of the time and all the novel's atmospheres. But beneath it all, there was this majestic progression, from the first scene to the denouement, the moving camera conducting us like a slow tragic theme tune that recalls a symphony. No TV camera has ever been so complicit and seductive, never has TV been so romantic\".<ref>{{cite book |last=Wajnman |first=Solange  |title=Miniss\u00e9ries hist\u00f3ricas e a comunica\u00e7\u00e3o por objetos. Notas sobre os figurinos e cen\u00e1rios de 'Primo Bas\u00edlio' e \"Os Maias\"  |publisher=Universidade de Santa Maria (UFSM)|date=2011|url= https://periodicos.ufsm.br/animus/article/viewFile/4125/2624}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observatoriodaimprensa.com.br/artigos/qtv31012001991.htm|title=Os Maias|author=Luis Fernando Ver\u00edssimo|date=26 January 2001|publisher=Observat\u00f3riodaImprensa.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Para Os Maias, Carvalho escolheu um andamento que, na m\u00fasica, seria chamado de \u2018andante majestoso\u2019, que pode impacientar a gera\u00e7\u00e3o videoclipe, mas est\u00e1 perfeito, e era o ritmo preferido de Lean e Visconti.}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)'' ===\n{{Main|Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria}}\nOver two seasons, ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]'' (2005), a mini-series in which he was also responsible for creation and script, consolidated the director's linguistic research.<ref>\"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria - segunda jornada \u00e9 uma joia lapidada com meticulosidade por um artista barroco, que n\u00e3o tem medo de abra\u00e7ar o excesso de refer\u00eancias universais e regionais para recriar a realidade brasileira com rigor e paix\u00e3o\", in \"Correio Braziliense\" (15 October 2005)</ref>  His co-writers were Luis Alberto de Abreu and Carlos Alberto Soffredini, basing themselves on a selection of stories taken from popular Brazilian oral storytelling tradition,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0901200511.htm|title=Carvalho invoca a cultura popular em micross\u00e9rie|author=Valmir Santos|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=9 January 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"\"Diretor associa \"Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria\" a uma busca pela identidade brasileira\"}}</ref> collected by the writers [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]], [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]] and [[Silvio Romero]]. Art direction by Lia Renha, guest artist Raimundo Rodriguez, direction of photography by Jos\u00e9 Tadeu Ribeiro and costumes by Luciana Buarque. The 60 marionettes that represented the animals were produced by the Grupo Giramundo, from Minas Gerais state. The work marked the start of the partnership between the director and psychoanalyst Carlos Byington, as advisor on the mythological dramatization of the text. The mini-series was conceived under a 360\u00ba dome, scrap from a rock show stage. The sound track, by Tim Rescala, was based on cirandas (traditional dances) by [[Heitor Villa-Lobos]], [[C\u00e9sar Guerra-Peixe]] and [[Francisco Mignone]]. Designer Jum Nakao was responsible for some of the costumes, with animation of the stop-motion scenes by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]]. It received the 2005 APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critics' Choice Award, the ABC Best Photography Award, the Contigo Award for Best Director and Best Child Actress and the Brazil Quality Award (Pr\u00eamio Qualidade Brasil ) for Best Director, Television \u2013 Best Special Project, Best Author and Best Breakthrough Actress, and reached the finals of the 2005 [[International Emmy Award]], in the categories Best Mini-Series and Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/folha/ilustrada/ult90u54506.shtml|title=Atriz mirim de \"Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria\" \u00e9 indicada ao Emmy\"|publisher=Folha Online|date=21 October 2005|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> It was nominated Hors Concours by the [[Banff World Media Festival]], in Canada (2006), and the [[International Public Television Screening Conference|Input International Board Taipei]] (2005). Compared with ''To the Left of the Father'' on account of its innovative television language, it caught the attention of critics and public by its novel, theatrical and playful language in transporting the universe of popular culture to a sophisticated television production, without losing its authenticity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acervo.oglobo.globo.com/busca/?tipoConteudo=pagina&ordenacaoData=relevancia&allwords=hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+maria&anyword=&noword=&exactword=&decadaSelecionada=2000&anoSelecionado=2005&mesSelecionado=10&revistaoglobo=on|title= Em Busca da nossa inf\u00e2ncia brasileira|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista OGlobo|date=9 October 2005|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=As imagens de Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria s\u00e3o raras. Tudo escapa ao padr\u00e3o global: \u00e9 fic\u00e7\u00e3o que tem coragem de se revelar como fic\u00e7\u00e3o, \u00e9 uma TV que tem a ousadia de buscar nas origens do cinema a reinven\u00e7\u00e3o da linguagem}}</ref> The critic Nilson Xavier considers it one of the most poetic, original and beautiful productions of recent years.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.teledramaturgia.com.br/hoje-e-dia-de-maria/ |title=Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=Site Teledramaturgia |access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Jean-Philippe Tess\u00e9, in the French magazine [[Cahiers du Cin\u00e9ma]], the mini-series was very ambitious and formally very well produced, following other noteworthy projects such as ''The Maias (Os Maias)''.\n\n=== ''Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)'' ===\n{{Main Article|:pt:A Pedra do Reino}}\nIn 2007, the director's third production based on the works of [[Ariano Suassuna]] brought to the TV the ''Romance d'A Pedra do Reino e o Pr\u00edncipe do Sangue do Vai-e-Volta''. The mini-series is regarded as yet another aesthetic innovation by the director, as in ''To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)'' and ''Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria)''. The script was the work of Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in collaboration with Luis Alberto de Abreu and Braulio Tavares, direction of photography by Adrian Teijido, scenography by Jo\u00e3o Irenio Maia, editing by Marcio Hashimoto and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. Regional artists, coordinated by the artist Raimundo Rodriguez, assisted with the art production. Music by Ant\u00f4nio Madureira (Quinteto Armorial) and Marco Ant\u00f4nio Guimar\u00e3es ([[Uakti (band)|Uakti]]). The cast was the fruit of the director's extensive search for talent throughout the backcountry (sert\u00e3o) of the Northeast. Television debut of the actors [[Irandhir Santos]] and Mayana Neiva and the singer Renata Rosa, among many others. It was filmed in the town of Tapero\u00e1, where [[Ariano Suassuna]] spent his childhood. During the coaching process, the team and cast attended lectures, out in the sert\u00e3o, by the actress [[Fernanda Montenegro]], the psychoanalyst Carlos Byington and the writer himself. [[Ariano Suassuna]] affirmed that Luiz Fernando Carvalho's recreation of his ''Romance d\u2019A Pedra do Reino'' resulted in an \"extraordinarily beautiful work that moved him as author and individual, as a spectator\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.revistacinetica.com.br/pedradoreinoilana.htm|title=A Pedra do Reino:A opera mundi de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Ilana Felman|publisher=Revista Cin\u00e9tica|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://ricardocalil.ig.com.br/index.php/2007/06/06/triunfo-da-imaginao/comment-page-1|title=Triunfo da Imagina\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Ricardo Calil|publisher=iG |date=6 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=A Pedra do Reino segue mesmo a l\u00f3gica dos sonhos, com del\u00edrios visuais de intenso brilho e elipses de tempo, com desorienta\u00e7\u00f5es espaciais e suspens\u00f5es de sentido}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/leia-critica-da-microsserie-pedra-do-reino-4182728|title=cr\u00edtica da micross\u00e9rie 'A Pedra do Reino|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 June 2007|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=\u201cA Pedra do Reino\u201d eleva \u00e0 en\u00e9sima pot\u00eancia um questionamento autoral onipresente nas hist\u00f3rias de Carvalho desde que rodou \u201cOs homens querem paz\u201d, um especial, exibido em 1991}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entretenimento.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/24/diretor-de-a-pedra-do-reino-adaptara-fernando-e-isaura-para-a-tv.amp.htm|title=Diretor de \"A Pedra do Reino\" adaptar\u00e1 \"Fernando e Isaura\" para a TV|author=Andr\u00e9ia Rocha|publisher=UOL|date=24 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/11/1934597-editora-lanca-dois-volumes-de-obra-postuma-de-ariano-suassuna.shtml|title=Nova Fronteira lan\u00e7a dois volumes de obra p\u00f3stuma de Ariano Suassuna|author=Claudio Leal |date=11 November 2017|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Portando nomes reais ou acrescidos de sobrenomes ficcionais, amigos surgem em ep\u00edgrafes e s\u00e3o incorporados pelo escritor como personagens dos di\u00e1logos sobre a cultura brasileira e seu projeto liter\u00e1rio. As atrizes Inez Viana e Marieta Severo , os diretores Aderbal Freire Filho e Luiz Fernando Carvalho, os poetas Jos\u00e9 Laurenio de Melo e Ad\u00e9lia Prado se situam entre esses interlocutores de Dom Pantero na \"Autobiografia Musical, Dan\u00e7arina, Po\u00e9tica, Teatral e V\u00eddeo-CinematoGr\u00e1fica\"}}</ref>\n\n=== Quadrante Project (Projeto Quadrante) ===\nBased on ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]'' (2007), the director set up the Quadrante Project with the intention of making a series of regional drama programs to rediscover the Brazilian imaginary through adaptations of literary texts of authors from each Brazilian state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq1712200617.htm|title=Sert\u00e3o \u00e9 \"semente\" de \"A Pedra do Reino\"|author=Esther Hamburguer|publisher=Revista Cult|date=17 December 2006|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> Similarly, local actors act out the texts. The richness of the project lay in the discovery of regional talent: authors, actors, composers, artists in general. The project recognized the human potential of each regional culture, looking beyond the simplistic image of a postcard. In addition to ''Stone of the Kingdom'', the Quadrante is made up of the mini-series [[Capitu]] (2008), based on the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]], and ''Dois Irm\u00e3os'' (2017), by [[Milton Hatoum]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/dois-irmaos-retoma-antigo-projeto-artistico-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-e-tem-primeiro-capitulo-deslumbrante|title=Dois Irm\u00e3os retoma antigo projeto art\u00edstico de Luiz Fernando Carvalho e tem primeiro cap\u00edtulo deslumbrante|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio da Televis\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Capitu'' ===\n{{Main|Capitu}}\nIn 2008, Luiz Fernando Carvalho directed and finalized the script for this adaptation of the book ''[[Dom Casmurro]]'', by [[Machado de Assis]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Rereading Dom Casmurro - aesthetic hybridity in Capitu  |publisher=University of Virginia|date=2014|url= http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?pid=S1983-68212014000100004&script=sci_arttext&tlng=pt}}</ref> The mini-series was written by Euclydes Marinho in collaboration with Daniel Piza, Luis Alberto de Abreu and Edna Palatnik. Art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez, photography by Adrian Teijido and costumes by Beth Filipecki. Colorist Sergio Pasqualino. It marked the TV debut of actors [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]] and Michel Melamed, among others. The mini-series was filmed in the abandoned Autom\u00f3vel Clube building, in downtown Rio de Janeiro, and the whole scenographic universe was created from newspaper and recycled material. The opening credits scene was conceived by the director and created by the designer Carlos B\u00eala.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/2475349/|title=Abertura de Capitu|author=Carlos B\u00eala|publisher=Vimeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The production is part of the Quadrante Project and was the director's tribute to [[Machado de Assis]] on the centenary of his death. It received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Critic's Choice Award (2009), ABC Best Photography Award  (from the Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) and the [[Creative Review]] award in the Best in Book and Design and Art Director categories. In the opinion of critic Gustavo Bernardo, the mini-series deserves \"to be viewed and reviewed countless times, at least because each fragment of a scene is precious for its beauty\".<ref>{{cite web| url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-capitu-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-145085.html|title=A Capitu de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Gustavo Bernardo|publisher=O Globo|date=9 December 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to theatre director [[:pt:Gabriel Villela|Gabriel Villela]], Luiz Fernando Carvalho produces works of art on the screen, calls on the viewer's vivacity so that he accepts nothing masticated, but masticates along with Casmurro.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/fsp/ilustrad/fq0808200923.htm|title=\"Capitu\" traduz para TV modo de narrar de Machado de Assis|author=Gabriel Villela|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|date=8 August 2009|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> For Randall Johnson, director of the UCLA Latin American Institute, \"Luiz Fernando Carvalho is today, without doubt, the director whose work is the most authorial of all TV and cinema production in Brazil\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/curso-na-universidade-da-california-debate-obra-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho-3144586|title=Curso na Universidade da Calif\u00f3rnia debate obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Mar\u00edlia Martins|publisher=Revista da TV/OGlobo|date=24 May 2009|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://renatofelix.wordpress.com/2009/08/27/entrevistas-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Entrevistas: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Renato Felix|publisher=Blog do Renato Felix|date=27 August 2009|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Trata-se um ensaio sobre a d\u00favida. N\u00e3o absolvo Capitu e n\u00e3o a condeno}}</ref>\n\n== 2010s ==\n\n=== ''After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?}}\nIn 2010, Luiz Fernando Carvalho created, directed and wrote the mini-series inspired by [[Sigmund Freud]]'s: famous question \"What does a woman want?\". [[Jo\u00e3o Paulo Cuenca]], Cecilia Giannetti and [[:pt:Michel Melamed|Michel Melamed]] collaborated on the script. As well as acting in the production, Melamed created the opening sound track. Direction of Photography Adrian Teijido, costumes by Beth Filipecki and art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez. The director launched actress [[Bruna Linzmeyer]]\u2019s career in this production. Osmar Prado shared the part of Freud with a model animated by Cesar Coelho, founder of the [[Anima Mundi (event)|Anima Mundi festival]], using the stop-motion technique.  The opening vignette features the work of German artist [[Olaf Hajek]], who also produced special illustrations for the mini-series by invitation of the director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/17214632|title=Abertura da miniss\u00e9rie \"Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?\"|author=Alexandre Romano|publisher=V\u00edmeo|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> It received the ABC award (Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira de Cinematografia) for Best Photography. According to columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, \"it is an oneiric journey, a visual poem that blends realities, full of references to times past, to what has been experienced, to what lingers in memory\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2010/11/critica-afinal-que-querem-as-mulheres-340331.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Afinal, o que querem as mulheres?|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=13 November 2010|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Carter |first=Eli Lee  |title=Afinal, o que Querem as Mulheres?: Luiz Fernando Carvalho's Metafictional Critique of Brazilian Television Fiction |journal=Journal of Latin American Cultural Studies |volume=23 |issue=4 |pages=363\u2013379 |date=2014|doi=10.1080/13569325.2014.958660 }}</ref>\n\n=== ''Suburbia'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Suburbia}}\nIn 2012, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated in TV drama a production in which all the protagonists are of African descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/critica/2012/11/01/seriado-olha-com-realismo-mas-carinho-para-a-dura-vida-no-suburbio.htm|title=Seriado olha com realismo, mas carinho para a dura vida no sub\u00farbio|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/suburbia-uma-entrevista-com-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Suburbia: uma entrevista com Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Luiz Zanin|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=3 November 2012|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> The mini-series, created and written by the director in partnership with Paulo Lins, counted on the collaboration of Adrian Teijido (Photography), Luciana Buarque (Costumes), Marcio Hashimoto (Editing) and Sergio Pasqualino (Colorist). It also marked the start of another research cycle, in which the director focused on realist aesthetics, which influenced the language as a whole, but mainly in the choice of non-actors for the main parts. The nearly 40 actors launched in the mini-series include artists of the groups N\u00f3s do Morro and [[:pt:Afroreggae|Afroreggae]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2012/12/critica-naturalidade-e-ausencia-de-pose-o-mundo-de-suburbia.html|title=Naturalidade e aus\u00eancia de pose: o mundo de 'Suburbia'|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=3 December 2012|access-date=24 April 2017}}</ref> \u00c9rika Januza, until then secretary of a school in the interior of Minas Gerais state, was chosen to play the main character of the story. Guest appearance by Fabr\u00edcio Boliveira, Rosa Marya Colin, Haroldo Costa, Maria Salvadora, Paulo Tiefenthaler and Dani Ornellas, among others. In 2012, the Globo network took the series up again for a second season in 2013 due to its satisfactory audience ratings. Later, however, the director Luiz Fernando Carvalho chose to cancel the new season. In the opinion of anthropologist Luiz Eduardo Soares, the work was a \"reconstructive reading of the carioca society, producing a superb result \".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-eduardo-soares-escreve-sobre-intensidade-da-forma-em-suburbia-6733970|title=Luiz Eduardo Soares escreve sobre a intensidade da forma em 'Suburbia'|author=Luiz Eduardo Soares|publisher=O Globo|date=15 November 2011|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Ladie\u2019s Mail (Correio Feminino)''===\n{{Main|:pt:Correio Feminino}}\nA mini-series in eight episodes, created and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho based on women's journals written by [[Clarice Lispector]] in the 1950s and 1960s, under the pseudonym Helen Palmer. The visual language and narrative were based on 60s pop art and design,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/quero-um-novo-ciclo-na-tv-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho-10375021|title='Quero um novo ciclo na TV', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|publisher=O Globo|date=16 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> from the costumes to the lighting and set; all filmed in a single light box, which changed color according to the subjects addressed. Adapted by Maria Camargo, the series was shown in 2013 as part of the program Fant\u00e1stico,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/luiz-fernando-carvalho-dirige-serie-correio-feminino-estreia-deste-domingo-do-fantastico-10543381|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho dirige s\u00e9rie Correio Feminino, estreia deste domingo do Fant\u00e1stico|author=Zean Bravo|publisher=O Globo|date=27 October 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref> with costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie and Luciana Buarque, photography by Mikeas and edited by Marcio Hashimoto. The actress [[Maria Fernanda C\u00e2ndido]] played Helen Palmer narrating all the episodes. In the cast, [[Luiza Brunet]] interpreted the mature woman, and [[:pt:Alessandra Maestrini|Alessandra Maestrini]], the young woman. The adolescent is [[Cintia Dicker]], an international model whose acting career was launched in the mini-series. In the opinion of critic Patricia Kogut, the series is \"inspired, pleasant, in good taste and unpretentious, like Clarice's texts as Helen Palmer\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/11/correio-feminino-faz-leitura-inspirada-de-clarice-lispector.html|title='Correio feminino' faz leitura inspirada de Clarice Lispector|author=Patricia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=5 November 2013|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Alexandre and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)'' ===\n{{Main|:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)}}\nA 2013 telefilm, with script by Luis Alberto de Abreu and Luiz Fernando Carvalho<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/prosa/post/a-consciencia-dos-sonhos-por-luiz-fernando-carvalho-518115.html|title=A consci\u00eancia dos sonhos - Diretor de 'Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is', especial de TV baseado nas hist\u00f3rias infantojuvenis de Graciliano Ramos, examina dimens\u00f5es m\u00edtica, ut\u00f3pica e humana na obra do alagoano|author=Luiz Fernando Carvalho|publisher=OGlobo|date=14 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> based on two stories by the Alagoan writer [[Graciliano Ramos]]. Luiz Fernando Carvalho's coaching and directing of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation to [[Marcelo Serrado]] and [[Ney Latorraca]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atarde.uol.com.br/cultura/televisao/noticias/1555977-ney-latorraca-e-destaque-em-alexandre-e-outros-herois|title=Ney Latorraca \u00e9 destaque em 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|date=16 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=A Tarde|author=Roberta Pennafort}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://f5.folha.uol.com.br/celebridades/2013/12/1383371-ney-latorraca-renasce-em-especial-na-tv-alexandre-e-outros-herois.shtml|title=Ney Latorraca renasce em especial na TV 'Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is'|author=Gislaine Gutierre|publisher=Folha Online|date=10 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Ele (Luiz Fernando Carvalho) me tirou totalmente da zona de conforto}}</ref> as well as a harmony in the quality of the interpretations. Direction of photography by Mickeas, art direction by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Luciana Buarque. Incidental sound track by Tim Rescala. Opening theme by the Pernambucan Siba. The cast of the TV special, a finalist in the 2014 [[International Emmy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/finalista-do-emmy-internacional-alexandre-outros-herois-pode-ter-mais-episodios-em-2015-14233742|title=Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is \u00e9 finalista do Emmy Internacional|date=14 October 2014|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Revista da TV|author=Nilton Carauta}}</ref> also included Fl\u00e1vio Bauraqui, Fl\u00e1vio Rocha, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and Luci Pereira.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/direcao-seca-faz-a-qualidade-tecnica-de-alexandre-e-outros-herois-1577#ixzz4dl00ba3T|title=Dire\u00e7\u00e3o 'seca' faz a qualidade t\u00e9cnica de Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is|date=19 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|author=Raphael Scire}}</ref> Critic Patricia Kogut considered the telefilm a miniature work of art on television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2013/12/alexandre-e-outros-herois-uma-pequena-obra-prima-na-globo.html|title='Alexandre e outros her\u00f3is': uma pequena obra-prima na Globo|date=20 December 2013|access-date=10 April 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|quote=Trata-se de uma viagem horizontal pela cultura popular, sem o olhar estrangeiro, ou a entroniza\u00e7\u00e3o daquilo que \u00e9 simples. Essa \u00e9 uma das maiores virtudes do programa adaptado por Lu\u00eds Alberto de Abreu e com a clar\u00edssima assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho. N\u00e3o vimos a alta cultura caindo na tenta\u00e7\u00e3o popularizante e sim uma produ\u00e7\u00e3o abertamente popular e ao mesmo tempo elegante e requintada, com ambi\u00e7\u00e3o art\u00edstica e dona de um universo est\u00e9tico pr\u00f3prio, original}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2013/12/25/luiz-fernando-carvalho-lembra-que-ha-lugar-para-graciliano-ramos-na-tv/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho lembra que h\u00e1 lugar para Graciliano Ramos na TV|author=Mauricio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=25 December 2013|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)'' ===\n{{Main|Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o}}\nThis 2014 production marked the director's return to the telenovela format after 12 years of dedicating himself to mini-series and more authorial projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2014/04/1445086-luiz-fernando-carvalho-critica-novelas-tradicionais-e-cruza-conto-de-fadas-e-hq.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho critica novelas tradicionais e cruza conto de fadas e HQ|author=Sylvia Colombo|publisher=Serafina|date=27 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://televisao.uol.com.br/noticias/redacao/2014/07/31/e-preciso-renovar-mais-e-copiar-menos-diz-diretor-de-meu-pedacinho.htm|title=\u00c9 preciso renovar mais e copiar menos, diz diretor de Meu Pedacinho|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' was written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa and directed by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, with art production by Marco Cortez, art work by Raimundo Rodriguez and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. The critics praised various aspects, from the harmony of the quality of acting to the editing, direction, costumes, scenography and aesthetics, inspired by Westerns and Japanese manga (comics).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://zh.clicrbs.com.br/rs/entretenimento/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estetica-que-deu-certo-4564521.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o: A Est\u00e9tica que deu certo|author=Vanessa Scalei|publisher=Zero Hora|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2014/08/01/meu-pedacinho-do-chao-fugiu-do-obvio-surpreendeu-e-encantou/|title=Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o fugiu do \u00f3bvio e surpreendeu|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=1 August 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/opiniao/cinco-motivos-para-tornar-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-inesquecivel-4268|title=Cinco motivos para tornar Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o inesquec\u00edvel|author=Raphael Scire|publisher=UOL|date=30 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/05/linda-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-dissolve-duvidas-da-estreia.html|title='Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o' dissolve d\u00favidas na estreia|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=27 May 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o \u00e9 uma das grandes produ\u00e7\u00f5es da nossa TV. Segue linda, artesanal dentro do poss\u00edvel e \u00e9 carregada principalmente por sua hist\u00f3ria. Dentro daquele ambiente on\u00edrico e l\u00edrico, h\u00e1 dramas e conflitos s\u00e9rios. Eles capturam a aten\u00e7\u00e3o do p\u00fablico com for\u00e7a. E a beleza dos cen\u00e1rios e figurinos n\u00e3o dissimula nem diminui esses recados}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,meu-pedacinho-de-chao-nao-se-acomoda-e-faz-nevar-no-rio,1531589|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o n\u00e3o se acomoda e faz nevar no Rio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=21 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Luiz Fernando Carvalho's direction of the actors revealed a new code of interpretation, noted by the critics, to actors such as [[Juliana Paes]] and [[Rodrigo Lombardi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/04/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-estreia-com-marca-do-diretor.html|title=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o estreia com marca do diretor (...) Juliana Paes, madura, exuberante, respondeu bem \u00e0 m\u00e3o forte da dire\u00e7\u00e3o. Mostrou que avan\u00e7ou um passo na sua trajet\u00f3ria de atriz}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching to shape the aesthetics of ''My Little Plot of Land'' took place at TVLi\u00ea, known as Galp\u00e3o, which operated from 2013 to 2017. The space brought together all the creative teams and was conceived by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, at Projac, for collaborative project creation and talent training. In addition to ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'', the works ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Female Messages (Correio Feminino)]]'', ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexander and Other Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'', ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' were created in the Galp\u00e3o. The whole process of creation and production of the novela in the Galp\u00e3o is described by the journalist Melina Dalboni in the book ''Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'', which has drawings, sketches and photos by the director and the team (published by Casa da Palavra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2015/02/13/livro-prolonga-a-experiencia-dos-fas-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao/|title=Livro prolonga experi\u00eancia dos f\u00e3s do Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|publisher=UOL|date=13 February 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Sets and costumes were envisaged through the playful eye of childhood,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/conheca-detalhes-da-criacao-de-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-trama-com-universo-onirico-ar-de-fabula-12586431|title=Conhe\u00e7a detalhes da cria\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Meu pedacinho de ch\u00e3o', trama com universo on\u00edrico e ar de f\u00e1bula|author=Nat\u00e1lia Castro|publisher=Revista da TV|date=26 June 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> and according to the columnist Patr\u00edcia Kogut, contributed to a beautiful invented universe, far different from what we are used to seeing on TV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2014/07/meu-pedacinho-de-chao-deixara-sua-marca-na-historia-da-televisao.html|title=Cr\u00edtica: Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o deixar\u00e1 sua marca na hist\u00f3ria da TV|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=O Globo|date=31 July 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The houses were faced with recycled cans, based on the work of artist Raimundo Rodriguez. The costumes, the subject of an exhibition, mixed technological fabrics and plastic material.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2014/12/exposicao-exibe-figurino-da-novela-meu-pedacinho-de-chao-no-rio.html|title=Exposi\u00e7\u00e3o exibe figurinos de Meu Pedacinho do Ch\u00e3o|publisher=G1|date=27 December 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> Cesar Coelho, of the Anima Mundi Festival, used stop-motion and time-lapse techniques for all the animation. The novela received the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]); Contigo Magazine Award for Best Child Actor (Tom\u00e1s Sampaio) and Best Director; the Extra television award  for Best Costumes and Best Makeup (Rubens Lib\u00f3rio); and the Quem Magazine award for Best Actor ([[Irandhir Santos]]), Best Supporting Actor (Johnny Massaro) and Best Author ([[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]]). The critic Cristina Padiglione regards the novela as worthy of a standing ovation, and in the opinion of Alexandra Moraes \"the images, at first sight childish, gain relevance with colors and effects of dramatic intent. Good performances and the firm hand of the director give the plot meaning\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/cristina-padiglione/isso-nao-e-um-pedacinho-de-chao-e-um-latifundio/|title=Isso n\u00e3o \u00e9 um 'pedacinho' de ch\u00e3o, \u00e9 um latif\u00fandio|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2014/04/1437903-critica-cores-e-filtros-reforcam-trama-em-meu-pedacinho-de-chao.shtml|title=Cr\u00edtica: Cores e filtros refor\u00e7am trama em 'Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o'|author=Alexandra Moraes|publisher=Ilustrada - Folha de S.Paulo|date=9 April 2014|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Old River (Velho Chico)'' ===\n{{Main|Velho Chico (telenovela)}}\nIn 2016, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' marked Luiz Fernando Carvalho's return to prime time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/velho-chico-folhetim-classico-mas-com-muita-renovacao.html|title='Velho Chico': folhetim cl\u00e1ssico, mas com muita renova\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico, como outras obras de Carvalho, provou que a ind\u00fastria cultural da televis\u00e3o tamb\u00e9m pode ter ares de artesanato. N\u00e3o \u00e9 pouco\"}}</ref> directing the novela written by [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]] and Bruno Luperi, which again carried the imprint of the new esthetic in TV drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://omelete.uol.com.br/series-tv/entrevista/velho-chico-stanley-kubrick-da-tv-brasileira-diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-novela/|title=\"Stanley Kubrick da TV brasileira\", diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a novela|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=14 March 2016|publisher=Omelete.com.br|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/01/1734731-a-maior-funcao-da-televisao-e-criar-cidadaos-diz-luiz-fernando-carvalho.shtml|title='A maior fun\u00e7\u00e3o da televis\u00e3o \u00e9 criar cidad\u00e3os', diz Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita|date=31 January 2016|publisher=Ilustrada|work=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=24 February 2016}}</ref> The novela was divided into two phases,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/06/velho-chico-tem-cenas-para-amarrar-o-presente-ao-passado.html |title='Velho Chico' tem cenas para amarrar o presente e o passado|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|date=15 June 2016|publisher=O Globo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> with direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso and costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie. Highlights were the photography<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-luiz-fernando-carvalho-fala-sobre-a-fotografia-peculiar-da-novela-velho-chico,10000064739|title=Diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho fala sobre a fotografia peculiar da novela 'Velho Chico'|author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=25 July 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho e a fotografia viscontiana da novela \u2018Velho Chico\u2019}}</ref> and acclaimed performances by the actors [[Antonio Fagundes]], Lucy Alves, [[Domingos Montagner]], Lee Taylor, [[Marcos Palmeira]], [[Chico Diaz]], Renato G\u00f3es, [[Rodrigo Lombardi]], [[Dira Paes]], [[Irandhir Santos]], [[Fabiula Nascimento]], Julia Dalavia, Cyria Coentro, Barbara Reis, Julio Machado, Umberto Magnani, [[Camila Pitanga]], [[Christiane Torloni]], [[Marcelo Serrado]], Gabriel Leone, Giulia Buscaccio, Mariene de Castro, G\u00e9sio Amadeu, Jos\u00e9 Dumont, Marc\u00e9lia Cartaxo and others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2016/12/quem-fez-festa-dos-telespectadores-em-2016.html|title=Quem fez a festa dos telespectadores em 2016|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=29 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u201cVelho Chico trouxe um vento novo para a faixa das 21h (...) Entre os destaques desse elenco estiveram novatos e veteranos, numa mistura de atores que encantou o p\u00fablico. Domingos Montagner, tragicamente morto perto da loca\u00e7\u00e3o, impressionou mais uma vez, como o Santo. Marcos Palmeira esteve no melhor papel da sua carreira. Antonio Fagundes, depois de ajustes no personagem, fez um coronel grandioso. Chico Diaz, Lucy Alves, Fabiula Nascimento, Zezita Matos, Christiane Torloni, Julia Dalavia, Renato G\u00f3es e tantos outros brilharam\"}}</ref> The cast was of a uniformity rarely seen in novelas, resulting in countless awards for its actors, including the APCA ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Arte]]) Award for Best Actress for Selma Egrei and the Critics' Choice Award for [[Domingos Montagner]](posthumous) and the production also won Best Supporting Actress (Selma Egrei), Best Supporting Actor (Irandhir Santos), Best Breakthrough Actress (Lucy Alves) and Best Breakthrough Actor (Lee Taylor),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/velho-chico-justica-selma-egrei-e-marco-ricca-sao-premiados-na-apc|title='Velho Chico', 'Justi\u00e7a', Selma Egrei e Marco Ricca s\u00e3o premiados na APCA|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Telepadi|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2016/11/1837325-aquarius-velho-chico-rita-lee-e-montagner-levam-premios-da-apca.shtml|title='Aquarius', 'Velho Chico', Rita Lee e Montagner levam pr\u00eamios da APCA|publisher=Folha Online|date=30 November 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> with Veja Rio's Carioca of the Year Award going to Luiz Fernando Carvalho for the renovated aesthetic of prime time television.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vejario.abril.com.br/cidades/luiz-fernando-carvalho-cria-uma-nova-estetica-para-o-horario-nobre/|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho cria uma nova est\u00e9tica para o hor\u00e1rio nobre|author=Sofia Cerqueira |publisher=Veja Rio|date=10 December 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The team's creative process and cast coaching lasted only three months and took place at TVli\u00ea, Luiz Fernando Carvalho's collaborative creative space, which operated at Projac between 2013 and 2017 and was known as Galp\u00e3o.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amarello.com.br/artigo/amarello-visita-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=Amarello Visita: Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Tom\u00e1s Biagi Carvalho|publisher=Amarello|access-date=14 April 2017|quote=Para preparar os atores de seus projetos, construiu um galp\u00e3o: uma mistura de circo com escola de samba, mambembe, feito de material reciclado e resto de cen\u00e1rio; uma c\u00e9lula criativa dentro dos Est\u00fadios Globo.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/serafina/2016/03/1743767-atores-de-velho-chico-nova-novela-da-globo-fazem-experiencias-em-galpao.shtml|title=Atores de 'Velho Chico' fazem experi\u00eancias em galp\u00e3o|author=L\u00edgia Mesquita |publisher=Serafina|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=Os personagens de todo o elenco da saga familiar escrita por Benedito Ruy Barbosa eram gestados em um espa\u00e7o coletivo de experimenta\u00e7\u00e3o idealizado pelo diretor Luiz Fernando Carvalho\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/lindo-capitulo-marca-volta-do-brasil-rural-21h.html|title=Lindo cap\u00edtulo marca a volta do Brasil rural \u00e0 TV|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=16 March 2016|quote=\"A estreia de ''Velho Chico'' teve mesmo o selo autoral do seu diretor, Luiz Fernando Carvalho.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/03/velho-chico-e-o-brasil-real-e-o-da-fantasia.html|title=Velho Chico e o Brasil real e o da fantasia|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=18 March 2016|quote=\"''Velho Chico'', de alguma forma, trouxe a f\u00e1bula de volta ao hor\u00e1rio nobre. (...) Mas a realiza\u00e7\u00e3o de Luiz Fernando Carvalho faz sonhar. E a hist\u00f3ria de Benedito Ruy Barbosa tem muitas chances de agradar com essa mistura de realidade \u00e1rida com estetiza\u00e7\u00e3o.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The first phase, applauded by the critics, marked the return of actor [[Rodrigo Santoro]] to the Globo fold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/rodrigo-santoro-volta-as-novelas-da-globo-17902522|title=Rodrigo Santoro volta \u00e0s novelas|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut|publisher=OGlobo|date=28 October 2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref>  and revealed the hitherto undiscovered talent of [[Carol Castro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/novelas/sensacao-de-velho-chico-carol-castro-teve-de-fazer-teste-chorando-10725 |title=Sensa\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico, Carol Castro teve de fazer teste chorando|author=Marcia Pereira|date=16 March 2016|publisher=Not\u00edcias da TV|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> [[Tarc\u00edsio Meira]], in just two episodes, put in an impressive performance, as did actress Selma Egrei, who took part in both phases of the novela.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.correio24horas.com.br/single-entretenimento/noticia/selma-egrei-se-destaca-em-velho-chico-com-a-sofrida-e-poderosa-encarnacao/?cHash=87ff234ae84127b9c7650a9a82598eae|title=Selma Egrei se destaca em 'Velho Chico' com a sofrida e poderosa Encarna\u00e7\u00e3o|author=Roberto Midlej |publisher=Correio Popular|date=7 August 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The cast was selected after an extensive  search for actors from the Northeast and marked the debut in novelas of Lucy Alves, Renato G\u00f3es, Marina Nery, Barbara Reis, Diyo Coelho, Xangai, Veronica Cavalcanti, Lee Taylor, Zezita de Matos, Mariene de Castro, Yara Charry, Raiza Alc\u00e2ntara, Lucas Veloso, Sueli Bispo and the comedian Bator\u00e9.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-tera-60-do-elenco-composto-por-atores-nordestinos-18716574|title=Velho Chico' ter\u00e1 60% do elenco composto por atores nordestinos|author=Zean Bravo |publisher=Revista da TV|date=28 February 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/televisao,diretor-procura-atores-por-todo-o-pais-para-novela-das-9,1777455|title=Diretor procura atores por todo o pa\u00eds para a novela das 9|author=Cristina Padiglione|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|date=2015|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref> The last chapters of the novela pay tribute to the actor [[Domingos Montagner]] (Santo), who drowned in the S\u00e3o Francisco river two weeks before the end of the serial. The character was maintained in the plot even after the actor's death through the language created by Luiz Fernando Carvalho, in which a single subjective camera interpreted Santo's viewpoint, so his presence was felt, engaging with all the other characters, to the end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/camera-subjetiva-solucao-de-velho-chico-para-santo-e-linda/ |title=C\u00e2mera subjetiva: solu\u00e7\u00e3o de 'Velho Chico' para Santo \u00e9 linda|author=Marcia Carolina Maia|date=27 September 2016|publisher=Veja|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mauriciostycer.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/obrigado-velho-chico/|title=Cr\u00edtica: Obrigado, \"Velho Chico\"|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=30 September 2016|publisher=UOL|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2016/09/presenca-incorporea-de-domingos-montagner-em-velho-chico.html|title=A Presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea de Domingos Montagner em Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=28 September 2016|quote=\"Nem dubl\u00ea, nem truques rasteiros. V\u00edtima de uma trag\u00e9dia que entristeceu o Brasil \u2014 e mais ainda a equipe de ''Velho Chico'' \u2014, Domingos Montagner estava na novela anteontem. Luiz Fernando Carvalho recorreu a uma c\u00e2mera subjetiva para trazer a presen\u00e7a incorp\u00f3rea do ator a quase todas as sequ\u00eancias. Era, claro, um recurso t\u00e9cnico. Por\u00e9m, qualquer car\u00e1ter racional foi plenamente absorvido pela dramaturgia e dissolvido pela emo\u00e7\u00e3o vis\u00edvel que dominou o elenco e alcan\u00e7ou o p\u00fablico. (...) Carvalho chegou perto de fronteiras perigosas e acertou muito mesmo.\"|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> The novela came under strong pressure from the Globo network's drama department, calling for modifications to the text, storyline and esthetics. The director and the author, [[:pt:Benedito Ruy Barbosa|Benedito Ruy Barbosa]], stood firm and refused to make the changes to ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]''. The in-house crisis made the TV columns and was described as a form of public pressure on Luiz Fernando Carvalho. According to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' is a landmark in the recent history of Brazilian TV, on account of its esthetic ambition and cultural relevance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2016/10/1818880-velho-chico-marcou-pela-ambicao-estetica-e-a-relevancia-cultural.shtml |title='Velho Chico' marcou pela ambi\u00e7\u00e3o est\u00e9tica e a relev\u00e2ncia cultural|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer|date=1 October 2016|publisher=Folha de S.Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017}}</ref> According to Nilson Xavier, the novela \u201chad incontestable technical and artistic quality, from the direction to the photography, sound track and the actors\u2019 performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2016/09/30/o-maior-merito-de-velho-chico-foi-provocar-e-estimular-o-publico/|title=O maior m\u00e9rito de Velho Chico foi provocar e estimular o p\u00fablico|author=Nilson Xavier|publisher=UOL|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\u00c9 de Boni (Jos\u00e9 Bonif\u00e1cio de Oliveira Sobrinho) a frase: \u201cA televis\u00e3o deve andar sempre um passo \u00e0 frente do p\u00fablico.\u201d \u201cVelho Chico\u201d foi um bom exemplo\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://extra.globo.com/tv-e-lazer/telinha/critica-sobre-fim-de-velho-chico-tintas-fortes-do-inicio-ao-fim-20212649.html|title=Cr\u00edtica de Velho Chico: tintas fortes do in\u00edcio ao fim|author=Carla Bittencourt|publisher=Extra|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017|quote=\"Velho Chico\u201d sempre foi uma novela de atua\u00e7\u00f5es e cenas memor\u00e1veis (...). Tudo muito denso, pintado com tintas mais fortes do que o telespectador est\u00e1 acostumado a ver nesse hor\u00e1rio. Essas caracter\u00edsticas garantiram \u00e0 trama seu lugar na hist\u00f3ria da teledramaturgia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2016/09/final-de-velho-chico-emociona-com-brilhante-atuacao-de-antonio-fagundes|title=Final de Velho Chico emociona com brilhante atua\u00e7\u00e3o de Antonio Fagundes|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=30 September 2016|access-date=17 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|title=Noveleiro|publisher=O Globo|author=Luis Fernando Verissimo|date=1 May 2016|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=\"Eu j\u00e1 tentava ver tudo o que Luiz Fernando Carvalho fazia, e n\u00e3o apenas por solidariedade de xar\u00e1. O que ele est\u00e1 fazendo no ''Velho Chico'' ultrapassa tudo o que j\u00e1 fez na TV - com a poss\u00edvel exce\u00e7\u00e3o de ''Os Maias''. Ele \u00e9 incapaz de um enquadramento que n\u00e3o seja perfeito, e teve tamb\u00e9m o talento de escolher um elenco perfeito.\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201032703/http://noblat.oglobo.globo.com/cronicas/noticia/2016/05/miss-bumbum.html|archive-date=1 December 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> It competed for the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://upload.iemmys.tv/public/iemmys/Nominees.aspx?nc=I|title=Nominees Categories|publisher=Iemmys.tv|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/kenneth-branagh-anna-friel-international-emmy-nominations-1202574242/|title=Kenneth Branagh, Anna Friel Receive International Emmy Nominations|publisher=Variety|author=Stewart Clarke|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4854403/emmy-nominations-2017/|title=Here Are the 2017 Emmy Nominations|publisher=Time|author=Kate Samuelson |date=13 July 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/revista-da-tv/velho-chico-justica-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional-21876053|title=Velho Chico e Justi\u00e7a concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=Revista da TV,O Globo|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://gshow.globo.com/programas/video-show/noticia/justica-ta-no-ar-velho-chico-totalmente-demais-e-alemao-concorrem-ao-emmy-internacional.ghtml|title=Justi\u00e7a, T\u00e1 no ar, Velho Chico, Totalmente Demais e Alem\u00e3o concorrem ao Emmy Internacional|publisher=GShow|date=27 September 2017|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/a-contradicao-de-velho-chico-novela-e-finalista-ao-emmy-mas-nao-cabe-no-catalogo-de-vendas-internacionais/|title=A contradi\u00e7\u00e3o de Velho Chico: novela \u00e9 finalista ao Emmy mas n\u00e3o cabe no cat\u00e1logo de vendas internacionais|publisher=Telepadi|date=27 September 2017|quote=\u00c9 quase uma contradi\u00e7\u00e3o que o enredo n\u00e3o tenha apelo internacional e que, inscrito no Emmy Internacional, na categoria de novelas, esteja entre os cinco finalistas|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/coluna/noticia/2017/11/rodrigo-santoro-participara-do-emmy-com-equipe-de-velho-chico.html|title=Rodrigo Santoro participar\u00e1 do Emmy com equipe do Velho Chico|publisher=O Globo|author = Patricia Kogut|date=14 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho, convidado pela Globo, n\u00e3o poder\u00e1 ir: est\u00e1 filmando em S\u00e3o Paulo|access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Lavoura Arcaica, 15 years on'' ===\nTribute was paid to the film ''[[To the Left of the Father]]'' in 2017, 15 years after it was made and on account of it being hailed as one of the most important Brazilian films of all time, at the [[Rio International Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-renasce-15-anos-apos-sua-estreia-no-festival-do-rio/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' renasce, 15 anos ap\u00f3s sua estreia, no Festival do Rio|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=23 September 2016|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|access-date=12 April 2017|quote=Um monumento cinematogr\u00e1fico de nossa Retomada}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.oglobo.globo.com/gente-boa/post/barulhinho-bom-exibicao-de-lavoura-arcaica-em-pelicula-faz-felicidade-dos-nostalgicos-no-festival-do-rio.html|title=Exibi\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica em pel\u00edcula faz a felicidade dos nost\u00e1lgicos no Festival do Rio |author=Cleo Guimaraes|date=15 October 2016|publisher=Gente Boa - OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Para Selton Mello, que interpreta o protagonista Andr\u00e9, \"Foi uma aventura emocional radical, que me tirou o ch\u00e3o e me fez renascer. Esse filme me deu coragem e a verdadeira dimens\u00e3o da minha profiss\u00e3o\u201d}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/noticias/cinema,lavoura-arcaica-e-homenageado-no-festival-do-rio,10000081767|title='Lavoura Arcaica' \u00e9 homenageado no Festival do Rio |author=Luis Carlos Merten|date=12 October 2016|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> and the [[S\u00e3o Paulo International Film Festival]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/lavoura-arcaica-com-presenca-de-radouan-nassar-poe-fim-a-mostra/|title='Lavoura Arcaica', com presen\u00e7a de Raduan Nassar, p\u00f5e fim \u00e0 Mostra|date=10 November 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Estado de S. Paulo|author=Luiz Zanin}}</ref> where a 35&nbsp;mm copy was shown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://revistacult.uol.com.br/home/lavoura-arcaica-e-a-utopia-por-um-mundo-melhor/|title=Lavoura Arcaica e a utopia por um mundo melhor|author=Eric Campi e Paulo Henrique Pompermaier|publisher=Revista Cult|access-date=14 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/lavoura-arcaica-15-anos-depois-dc69559029f7#.8409ildh4|title=Lavoura Arcaica, 15 anos depois|date=13 October 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/lavoura-arcaica-completa-15-anos-e-segue-arrebatador/|title='Lavoura Arcaica' completa 15 anos\u2026 e segue arrebatador|date=26 June 2016|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Estado de S. Paulo|author=Rodrigo Fonseca}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/quinze-anos-apos-estreia-lavoura-arcaica-dialoga-com-discussoes-atuais-20291697|title=Quinze anos ap\u00f3s a estreia, Lavoura Arcaica dialoga com discuss\u00f5es atuais |author=Suzana Velasco|date=15 October 2016|publisher=OGlobo|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> As part of the tribute at the [[Rio International Film Festival]], artist Raimundo Rodriguez created an installation that went on show for a month at the Esta\u00e7\u00e3o Net Botafogo, with memorabilia from the film, reviews and the director's notebooks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poltronapop.com.br/2016/10/festival-do-rio-2016-lavoura-arcaica.html|title=\"Lavoura Arcaica\" ganha exibi\u00e7\u00e3o e instala\u00e7\u00e3o de Raimundo Rodriguez|date=23 September 2016|publisher=PoltronaPop|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref> For Ismail Xavier and Ilana Feldman, Lavoura was born in 2001, emerging as a foreign body in the scenario of early 21st century Brazilian film, marked by its realism and its direct confrontation with Brazilian social and urban issues.<ref name=\"Ismail\"/>\n\n=== ''Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)'' ===\n{{Main|Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)}}\nScreened in 2017, the mini-series written by Maria Camargo based on the homonymous novel by [[Milton Hatoum]] was regarded by critics as another quality contribution to Brazilian television on account of the poetic style applied by the director to the adaptation of the novel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|title=Duas adapta\u00e7\u00f5es para Dois Irm\u00e3os: Entrevista com Milton Hatoum|publisher=Literasutra|author=Monalisa Marques|date=13 March 2017|access-date=20 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421001906/https://literasutra.com/2017/03/13/duas-adaptacoes-para-dois-irmaos-entrevista-com-milton-hatoum/|archive-date=21 April 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kogut.oglobo.globo.com/noticias-da-tv/critica/noticia/2017/01/dois-irmaos-faz-o-ano-comecar-muito-bem.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 um trabalho para ser louvado, uma grande contribui\u00e7\u00e3o de Carvalho para a televis\u00e3o brasileira|date=8 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=O Globo|author=Patr\u00edcia Kogut}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://operamundi.uol.com.br/conteudo/samuel/46161/em+adaptacao+de+dois+irmaos+para+tv+luiz+fernando+carvalho+transforma+prosa+de+milton+hatoum+em+poesia.shtml|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho conseguiu transformar a prosa de Hatoum em poesia|author=Vera Ceccarello |date=12 January 2017|publisher=OperaMundi|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffpostbrasil.com/edianez-parente/a-teatralidade-que-faz-de-dois-irmaos-uma-obra-prima-da-televi_a_21698413/|title=A teatralidade que faz de 'Dois Irm\u00e3os' uma obra prima da televis\u00e3o|author=Edianez Parente|date=13 January 2017|publisher=The Huffington Post|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/p-de-pop/dois-irmaos-e-a-versao-amazonica-de-caim-e-abel/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 a vers\u00e3o amaz\u00f4nica de Caim e Abel|author=Rodrigo Fonseca|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Pontuada por frases quase filos\u00f3ficas sobre a fala por vezes gaga do Tempo (outro muso de Carvalho), a vers\u00e3o de Maria Camargo para o romance de Hatoum deixa transbordante para o olhar quase teol\u00f3gico do aclamado diretor uma dimens\u00e3o b\u00edblica de fraternidade em f\u00faria, cindida na ponta da faca do ressentimento}}</ref> Direction of photography by Alexandre Fructuoso, costumes by Thanara Sch\u00f6nardie, scenography by Danielly Ramos, Juliana Carneiro and Mariana Villas-B\u00f4as, art production by Marco Cortez and Myriam Mendes. The production is part of the Quandrante Project and gained kudos with writer [[Milton Hatoum]]'s television debut.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://observador.pt/especiais/milton-hatoum-o-brasil-e-o-romance-da-desilusao/|title=Milton Hatoum: \"O Brasil \u00e9 o romance da desilus\u00e3o\"|author=Rita Cipriano |date=4 November 2017|publisher=Observador|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Milton Hatoum: \"O Luiz Fernando Carvalho \u00e9 um dos grandes diretores brasileiros. Dirigiu a adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de Lavoura Arcaica, do Raduan Nassar, e novelas importantes. A linguagem dele \u00e9 muito inovadora. N\u00e3o \u00e9 aquele pastel\u00e3o, aquele soap opera previs\u00edvel. Ele trabalha com uma linguagem muito criativa e pensa em tudo \u2014 nos figurinos, na luz, em cada detalhe. \u00c9 impressionante.\"}}</ref> According to the publishing house [[Companhia das Letras]], the book sales increased by some 500% after the start of the mini-series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gente.ig.com.br/tvenovela/2017-01-18/minisserie-dois-irmaos.html|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\": miniss\u00e9rie aumenta vendas do livro em mais de 500%|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=iG}}</ref> Careers launched in Two Brothers include actors Matheus Abreu (Omar and Yaqub as an adolescent), the indigenous Zahy Guajajara (the \u00edndia Domingas) and the singer Bruna Caram (R\u00e2nia in the adult phase). The Lebanese actor [[Mounir Maasri]] made a guest appearance in the mini-series and was also responsible for the prosody (stress patterns) of the cast. The quality of the acting of the whole cast was stressed by the critics and also on social media and reached the worldwide and Brazilian Trending Topics throughout the series: [[Eliane Giardini]] and [[Juliana Paes]] as Zana; [[Antonio Fagundes]] and Antonio Calloni as Halim; and [[Cau\u00e3 Reymond]] and Matheus Abreu as the twins Omar and Yaqub. It was filmed in 2015, but at the request of the Globo network, the director agreed to make the novela ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' before he finished editing ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Dois Irm\u00e3os]]'', which was shown in January 2017. A number of innovative relevant points in the director's language were highlighted: the relation between literature and the transposition into images,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/revista-bravo/a-linguagem-como-sonho-17e89674f18#.ue4tuyxkc|title=A Linguagem como Sonho|date=18 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Revista Bravo!|author=Almir de Freitas}}</ref> photography, framing, poetic language and sound track, which included hits from various decades to contextualize the period in which the mini-series was set. In addition, Luiz Fernando Carvalho inaugurated, on TV, the dialogue between the fictional scenes and images from the archives of Brazilian History, with the research of historical material done by Raquel Couto. \nAccording to the critic Maur\u00edcio Stycer, in an article published in the Folha de S.Paulo newspaper about Netflix's investment in Brazil, the miniseries was a startling revelation to those who normally only have access to terrestrial channels in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/mauriciostycer/2017/01/1852056-enquanto-netflix-avanca-na-conquista-do-mundo-globo-mostra-suas-armas.shtml|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" \u00e9 de uma qualidade espantosa para quem tem acesso apenas \u00e0 TV aberta no Brasil|date=21 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|author=Maur\u00edcio Stycer}}</ref> For Luiz Zanin, the miniseries was about Brazil and the thwarted ideal of a multi-ethnic, sensual and carefree nation. \u201cAn elegant delicacy served up to the public, and which will leave it wanting more\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.estadao.com.br/blogs/luiz-zanin/o-som-e-a-furia-em-dois-irmaos/|title=O Som e a F\u00faria de Dois Irm\u00e3os|author=Luiz Zanin|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Estad\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=Uma hist\u00f3ria bem contada fala de si mesma e tamb\u00e9m de outras coisas. Esta nos falou do Brasil, de sua utopia frustrada de na\u00e7\u00e3o multi\u00e9tnica, sensual e feliz. Um fino biscoito oferecido ao p\u00fablico, e que vai deixar saudades}}</ref> Critic Carlos Alberto de Mattos wrote that what was seen in The Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os) \u201cwas not a realistic reflection, but an exuberant image, a mythical saga, a work of art\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://carmattos.com/2017/01/09/arquetipos-e-epifanias-em-dois-irmaos/|title=Arqu\u00e9tipos e epifanias em Dois Irm\u00e3os|publisher=Rastros de Carmattos|author=Carlos Alberto Mattos|date=9 January 2017|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nilsonxavier.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2017/01/09/dois-irmaos-transmite-em-belas-imagens-um-crescente-clima-de-tragedia/|title='Dois Irm\u00e3os' transmite em belas imagens um crescente clima de trag\u00e9dia|author=Nilson Xavier|date=9 January 2017|publisher=UOL|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=(A miniss\u00e9rie) tem a assinatura de Luiz Fernando Carvalho, o que \u2013 j\u00e1 sabemos \u2013 significa esmero na est\u00e9tica, fotografia, tomadas, trilha sonora e dire\u00e7\u00e3o de atores.(...) Quem conhece a obra de Luiz Fernando Carvalho sabe que cada produ\u00e7\u00e3o sua \u00e9 \u00fanica, mesmo dentro de seu estilo caracter\u00edstico de dire\u00e7\u00e3o}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://revistacaju.com.br/2017/01/13/a-lavoura-amazonense-de-luiz-fernando-carvalho/|title=A 'lavoura amazonense' de Luiz Fernando Carvalho|author=Christiane Passafaro Guzzi|date=13 January 2017|publisher=Revista Caju|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=O que parece diferenciar Carvalho \u00e9 o estabelecimento de um estudo aprofundado da obra, da cr\u00edtica, da tradi\u00e7\u00e3o, e, principalmente, das reverbera\u00e7\u00f5es que a produ\u00e7\u00e3o dos escritores selecionados produzem no cen\u00e1rio ficcional}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/curioso-para-ver-dois-irmaos-ja-ha-3-episodios-no-globoplay-serie-vale-cada-minuto/|title=\"Dois Irm\u00e3os\" em duas palavras: n\u00e3o perca|date=6 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|author=Cristina Padiglione}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://veja.abril.com.br/entretenimento/dois-irmaos-tem-adaptacao-sensivel-e-poetica-na-globo/|title=Carvalho volta a exibir seu estilo teatral, sens\u00edvel e po\u00e9tico na adapta\u00e7\u00e3o|date=9 January 2017|access-date=23 February 2017|publisher=Veja|author=Meire Kusumoto}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observatoriodatelevisao.bol.uol.com.br/critica-de-tv/2017/01/intensa-e-inquietante-dois-irmaos-fisga-o-publico-a-critica-e-prova-que-nao-e-preciso-ritmo-frenetico-para-fazer-sucesso|title=Intensa e inquietante, Dois Irm\u00e3os fisga o p\u00fablico, a cr\u00edtica e prova que n\u00e3o \u00e9 preciso ritmo fren\u00e9tico para fazer sucesso|author=Andr\u00e9 Santana|date=21 January 2017|publisher=Observat\u00f3rio de Televis\u00e3o|access-date=20 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nexojornal.com.br/entrevista/2017/01/12/%E2%80%98Dois-irm%C3%A3os%E2%80%99-%C3%A9-sobre-o-colapso-de-uma-fam%C3%ADlia.-Mas-tamb%C3%A9m-de-um-projeto-de-pa%C3%ADs|title='Dois irm\u00e3os' \u00e9 sobre o colapso de uma fam\u00edlia. Mas tamb\u00e9m de um projeto de pa\u00eds|author=Juliana Domingos de Lima|date=12 January 2017|publisher=Nexo Jornal|access-date=20 April 2017|quote=\"A adapta\u00e7\u00e3o de \u201cDois irm\u00e3os\u201d, na verdade uma transposi\u00e7\u00e3o ou transcri\u00e7\u00e3o para o audiovisual, (...) oferece ao espectador brasileiro a possibilidade de alguns encontros fundamentais: encontro com cinquenta anos de hist\u00f3ria do pa\u00eds (...); com uma enorme diversidade humana e cultural (...); com uma forma expressiva que investe na sensibilidade e intelig\u00eancia do espectador (...); por fim, o encontro com um projeto de pa\u00eds, que se insinuava durante a Belle \u00c9poque amaz\u00f4nica, mas cuja promessa de futuro \u00e9 posta abaixo pela ditadura civil-militar e sua ideia destrutiva de \u201cprogresso\u201d. (...) \u00c9 importante perceber que, enquanto a literatura brasileira ganha relev\u00e2ncia e contund\u00eancia ao migrar para a TV, a pr\u00f3pria TV ganha tamb\u00e9m enorme prest\u00edgio art\u00edstico ao valorizar um produto liter\u00e1rio nacional, ainda mais sob a marca e o estilo barroco, marcado pelo ac\u00famulo de elementos e alta intensidade, do Luiz Fernando Carvalho\" (Ilana Feldman)}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, Luiz Fernando Carvalho left the Globo Network (Rede Globo) after 30 years of working for the TV station.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://telepadi.com.br/desgastes-de-bastidores-motivaram-fim-do-contrato-do-diretor-de-dois-irmaos-na-globo/|title=Um diretor fora da curva|date=24 February 2017|publisher=Telepadi|access-date=28 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valor.com.br/cultura/4911882/um-diretor-fora-da-curva|title=Um diretor fora da curva|author=Maria da Paz Trefaut|date=24 March 2017|publisher=Valor Econ\u00f4mico|access-date=20 November 2017|quote=Luiz Fernando Carvalho construiu uma aura intelectual ao seu redor, uma imagem de profissional autoral que n\u00e3o se apega a conven\u00e7\u00f5es}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the director received the APCA Award for ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2017/12/1942551-apca-escolhe-os-melhores-de-2017.shtml|title=APCA escolhe os melhores de 2017|date=11 December 2017|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/pop-arte/noticia/juliana-paes-e-a-forca-do-querer-ganham-premio-da-associacao-paulista-de-criticos-de-artes-apca-veja-lista.ghtml|title=Juliana Paes e a For\u00e7a do Querer ganham pr\u00eamio da Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Paulista de Cr\u00edticos de Artes (APCA); veja a lista|date=12 December 2017|publisher=G1|access-date=3 January 2018}}</ref> the [[International Emmy Award for Best Telenovela]] Nomination for ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and the Bravo Award (Pr\u00eamio Bravo) for Artist of the Year, for his trajectory and esthetic renovation on television with ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' and ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' and the 15th anniversary of the film ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of The Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''.\n\n=== ''The Passion According to G.H. (A Paix\u00e3o Segundo G.H.)'' ===\n{{Main|The Passion According to G.H. (film)}}\nFor the centennial of the birth of [[Clarice Lispector]], in 2020, Carvalho is releasing a film adaptation based on the homonymous novel by the brazilian author.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/2018/11/apos-lavoura-arcaica-luiz-fernando-carvalho-adapta-obra-de-clarice.shtml|title=Ap\u00f3s Lavoura Arcaica, Luiz Fernando Carvalho adapta obra de Clarice|author=Guilherme Genestreti|date=28 November 2018|publisher=Folha de S. Paulo|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/luiz-fernando-carvalho-retoma-carreira-como-diretor-de-cinema-em-sp-22154367|title=Luiz Fernando Carvalho retoma carreira como diretor de cinema em SP|author=Alessandro Giannini|date=6 December 2017| publisher=O Globo|access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.folhadelondrina.com.br/colunistas/celia-musilli/iluminacoes-e-assombros-literarios-2979349e.html |title=Ilumina\u00e7\u00f5es e Assombros Liter\u00e1rios|author=Celia Musilli|date=11 January 2020|publisher=Folha de Londrina|access-date=30 January 2020}}</ref> Is the second feature film by the filmmaker after the award-winning [[To the Left of the Father]] (Portuguese: Lavoura Arcaica) (2001), also a cinematographic version of a classic of Brazilian literature. It was during the editing of \"Lavoura Arcaica\" that Luiz Fernando Carvalho had contact with G.H. - central novel of Clarice Lispector's work. The movie was entirely filmed in a penthouse of the neighbourhood of Copacabana, Rio de Janeiro, and presents [[Maria Fernanda Candido]] as the main character, G.H.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/filmes/maria-fernanda-candido-estara-em-versao-para-cinema-de-paixao-segundo-gh-22154286|title=Maria Fernanda C\u00e2ndido estar\u00e1 em vers\u00e3o para cinema de \"A Paix\u00e3o Segundo G.H.\"|author=Alessandro Giannini|date=6 December 2017| publisher=O Globo|access-date=29 January 2020|quote=\"Tenho uma afinidade grande com o Luiz. Esse aprofundamento que ele prop\u00f5e \u00e9 fundamental para realizarmos e desenvolvermos um trabalho. Gosto de como ele leva tudo isso e como prop\u00f5e o laborat\u00f3rio\".}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe was married to the artist Sandra Burgos, with whom he has one son, Th\u00e9o Burgos Carvalho.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Tereza Seiblitz]], with whom he has one son, Vitt\u00f3rio, born June 8, 2001.\n\nHe was married to the actress [[Let\u00edcia Persiles]], with whom he has one son, Ariel.\n\n== Bibliography ==\nThe following books written by Luiz Fernando Carvalho are references for this article. For the complete list of books about the director, see [[Luiz Fernando Carvalho Bibliography]]\n* {{cite book |first = Luiz Fernando |last = Carvalho | title = Sobre Lavour'Arcaica \u2013 O filme  | date = 2002  | publisher= Ateli\u00ea Editorial  | isbn = 9780815411833|url=https://books.google.com/?id=xNAed1GNO7QC&printsec=frontcover&dq=lavoura+arcaica#v=onepage&q=lavoura%20arcaica&f=false}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Abreu |first2=Luis Alberto |title=Hoje \u00e9 dia de Maria \u2013 Roteiros da 1a e 2a jornadas |publisher=Globo |date=2006 |isbn=9788525040985|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Qy8bAQAAIAAJ&q=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria&dq=Hoje+%C3%A9+dia+de+Maria}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= Pedra do Reino - Estojo Ilustrado com 5 Cadernos de Filmagens + Di\u00e1rio de Elenco e Equipe |publisher=Globo |date=2007 |isbn=978-8525043375|url=http://www.saraiva.com.br/pedra-do-reino-estojo-ilustrado-com-5-cadernos-de-filmagens-diario-de-elenco-e-equipe-1968247.html}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho|title= O processo de Capitu |publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra  |date=2008 |isbn=978-8577341023|url=https://books.google.com/?id=vaBaMQAACAAJ&dq=inauthor:%22Luiz+Fernando+Carvalho%22}}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando|last=Carvalho |title= Livro - Quem \u00e9 Capitu?|publisher= Nova Fronteira |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=17\u201320| isbn=9788520920831|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DuUdAQAAIAAJ&q=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&dq=Quem+%C3%A9+Capitu?&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj0-9O0ktTTAhWJl5AKHcKSBIIQ6AEIJjAA}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Diniz |first2=Julio|title= Machado de Assis (1908-2008) |publisher= Contraponto |date=2008 |chapter=Capitu c\u2019est moi? |pages=80\u201383|isbn=978-85-7866-011-6|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Machado_de_Assis.html?id=cyyFPgAACAAJ&redir_esc=y}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando|last2=Cuenca |first2=Jo\u00e3o Paulo |last3=Gianetti |first3=Cec\u00edlia |last4=Melamed |first4=Michel  |title= Afinal, o que querem as mulheres? |publisher= LeYa |date=2010 |isbn=9788580440300|url=https://books.google.com/?id=pwqCYgEACAAJ}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Carvalho |first1=Luiz Fernando |last2=Lins |first2=Paulo |last3=Franz |first3=Pedro |title=Suburbia |publisher=Aeroplano |date=2012 |isbn=9788578200916 |url=http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |access-date=2017-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171112022818/http://www.pedrofranz.com.br/suburbia |archive-date=2017-11-12 |url-status=dead }}\n* {{cite book |first=Luiz Fernando |last=Carvalho |title= Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|publisher= LeYa Casa da Palavra |date=2013 |isbn=978-85-7734-525-0|url=https://books.google.com/?id=sHngjgEACAAJ}}\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Cinema\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''The Waiting (A Espera)'' \n| Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Short-film]] based on [[Roland Barthes]]\u00b4s Fragments d'un discours amoureux\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[:pt:Que Teus Olhos Sejam Atendidos|May your eyes be blessed (Que Teus Ohos Sejam Atendidos)]]''\n| Director\n| [[Documentary film]]\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[To the Left of the Father|To the Left of the Father (Lavoura Arcaica)]]''\n|  Director and Screenwriter\n| [[Film]] based on the novel of [[Raduan Nassar]]\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The_Passion_According_to_G.H._(film)|The Passion According to G.H.]]''\n|  Director and Screenwriter\n|  [[Film]] based on the novel of [[Clarice Lispector]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+TV Series\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[:pt:Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas (miniss\u00e9rie)|Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]'' \n| Assistant director\n| Based on [[Guimar\u00e3es Rosa]]\u00b4s [[Grande Sert\u00e3o: Veredas]]\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''[[:pt:Riacho Doce (miniss\u00e9rie)|Sweet River (Riacho Doce)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Jos\u00e9 Lins do Rego]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[:pt:Os Maias (miniss\u00e9rie)|The Maias (Os Maias)]]''\n|  Director \n| Based on [[E\u00e7a de Queiroz]]\u00b4s [[Os Maias]]\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria|Today is Maria's Day (Hoje \u00c9 Dia de Maria)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[:pt:Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada|Today is Maria's Day: Second Journey (Hoje \u00e9 Dia de Maria: Segunda Jornada)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[M\u00e1rio de Andrade]], [[C\u00e2mara Cascudo]] and [[Silvio Romero]]\u00b4s essay; Co-written with Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[:pt:A Pedra do Reino|Stone of the Kingdom (A Pedra do Reino)]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel; Co-written with Braulio Tavares and Luis Alberto de Abreu\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Capitu]]''\n| Director and Screenwriter\n| Based on [[Machado de Assis]]\u00b4s [[Dom Casmurro]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[:pt:Afinal, o Que Querem as Mulheres?|After all, what does a woman want (Afinal, O Que Querem as Mulheres?)]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Influenced by [[Sigmund Freud]]\u00b4s theory; Co-written with J.P. Cuenca and Michel Melamed\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[:pt:Sub\u00farbia|Suburbia]]''\n| Novelist, Director and Screenwriter\n| Co-written with Paulo Lins\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Correio Feminino|Ladie's Mail (Correio Feminino)]]'' \n| Novelist e Diretor\n|  From [[Clarice Lispector]]\u00b4s chronicles\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Dois Irm\u00e3os (miniseries)|Two Brothers (Dois Irm\u00e3os)]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on [[Milton Hatoum]]\u00b4s novel\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Soap Opera\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Helena (1987)|Helena]]'' \n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Machado de Assis]]\n|-\n| 1987\n| ''[[:pt:Carmem (telenovela)|Carmen]]''\n|  Director\n| Written by [[Gl\u00f3ria Perez]]\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[:pt:Vida Nova|Vida Nova]]''\n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Tieta (telenovela)|Tieta]]''\n| Director\n| Based on the novel of [[Jorge Amado]]\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Pedra sobre Pedra|Stone on Stone (Pedra sobre Pedra)]]''\n| Director\n| Written by [[Aguinaldo Silva]]\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Renascer|Rebirth (Renascer)]]''\n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:Irm\u00e3os Coragem (1995)|Irm\u00e3os Coragem]]''\n| Director\n| Remake of [[Janete Clair]]\u00b4s soap opera\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[O Rei do Gado|The King of Catlle (O Rei do Gado)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Esperan\u00e7a (telenovela)|Esperan\u00e7a]]'' \n| Director \n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o|My Little Plot of Land (Meu Pedacinho de Ch\u00e3o)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa\n\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Velho Chico (telenovela)|Old River (Velho Chico)]]'' \n| Director\n| Written by Benedito Ruy Barbosa e Bruno Luperi\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Especiais para TV\n|-  \n!Year\n!Title\n!Credit\n!Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1990\n| ''Chit\u00e3ozinho e Xoror\u00f3 Especial'' \n| Director\n| Musical Show\n|-\n| 1991\n| ''The Cangaceiro's Revenge (Os Homens Querem Paz)'' \n| Director\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[:pt:Uma mulher vestida de sol|A Woman Clothed in Sun (Uma Mulher Vestida de Sol)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[:pt:A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a (TV)|The Farce of Pleasant Idleness (A Farsa da Boa Pregui\u00e7a)]]''\n|  Director\n| Based on [[Ariano Suassuna]]\u00b4s novel\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:pt:Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is (programa de TV)|Alexandre and Others Heroes (Alexandre e Outros Her\u00f3is)]]'' \n|  Diretor\n| Based on [[Graciliano Ramos]]\u00b4s short stories\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://luizfernandocarvalho.com/ Luiz Fernando Carvalho - Official website] {{in lang|pt}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=0142461|name=Luiz Fernando Carvalho}}* \n* [http://40.mostra.org/en/filme/3902-TO-THE-LEFT-OF-THE-FATHER To The Left of The Father - Mostra de Cinema de SP]\n* [http://www.commeaucinema.com/critiques/a-la-gauche-du-pere,14209 A La Gauche du Pere - Comme au Cinema] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.allocine.fr/film/fichefilm_gen_cfilm=46949.html A La Gauche du Pere - AlloCine] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://enciclopedia.i